msgid "92cba777c8bb49dc82e263fa4fd9e109"
msgstr "Thus have I heard, at one time,"

msgid "d1edca836684403ea7682f596dafbae0"
msgstr ""
"the Bhagavat was dwelling on the Vulture Peak Mountain in Rājgir, on a "
"summit of infinite gems, in the Womb of Dharmadhātu Palace,"

msgid "86734b9ef86d4eacbcfe8f45c256b212"
msgstr ""
"together with a great assembly of twenty-five thousand monks. All of them "
"were arhats who had exhausted their outflows."

msgid "652bfa78f5a448cca78f9efdfe813804"
msgstr "They were without afflictions and controlled."

msgid "15e4dfc1476c42c483aceb65584e1e39"
msgstr "Their minds were perfectly liberated,"

msgid "e8414e7246d944799c0d5269e610c8f7"
msgstr "and their wisdom was perfectly free."

msgid "d1330b7fbbaa4791941b5ffb9f5a780f"
msgstr ""
"They were knowledgeable great elephants who had accomplished what needed to "
"be done."

msgid "8f081969afb546c99e95ee685dbea267"
msgstr "They had laid down their burden and fulfilled their own benefit."

msgid "e2a02708ffae47579ed441886898eb02"
msgstr "They had destroyed the bonds of existence and,"

msgid "5e7c998173474b69b84a7d712884ce66"
msgstr ""
"thanks to their correct knowledge, their minds were perfectly liberated."

msgid "4294b3b5ad654ab6bab1bf5ecd8e20dc"
msgstr "youthful Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "5e6a7b3b8b9b482ba8003d47180c0e14"
msgstr "Dhanaśrī,"

msgid "876a113cee9847db8902628ddc17b180"
msgstr "Buddhiśrī,"

msgid "27f758cadb3e49f9bfbd7622345f7605"
msgstr "Bhaiṣajyarāja, and"

msgid "5d56fa52a6e7438697de5bb462ac961e"
msgstr "Bhaiṣajya­samudgata."

msgid "cc3f851b4daf444ca1078cd1c5c6c738"
msgstr "All of them were turning the Dharma wheel that does not turn back."

msgid "3fc5677430884d76b1b00a61c8b4fb15"
msgstr ""
"They were skilled in inquiring about the vaipulya sūtras of the Heap of "
"Jewels and"

msgid "dea5e0ee1c6344e79763b12c5924f1b6"
msgstr "and had obtained the level called Cloud of Dharma."

msgid "8acc28834f08464b9396007e9b5666ce"
msgstr "In terms of wisdom, they were like Sumeru,"

msgid "c046a1af8c944529b035f9b2e8eda214"
msgstr ""
"and all of them had thoroughly cultivated the dharmas of emptiness, no sign,"
" no wish, no arising, no birth, and no existence."

msgid "d390734f4c3a42f8a5de86d729233cd3"
msgstr "The greatly profound Dharma appeared to them ,"

msgid "b4b04e878b2f4e55b3b17064dae87abb"
msgstr "and they had the postures of the tathāgatas."

msgid "958b69344f1b49cea923d1356e0a7129"
msgstr ""
"In other world spheres, they had been sent out by quintillions of "
"tathāgatas."

msgid "3b183158b82742468e98a7e75f4e7b11"
msgstr ""
"All of them were fully clairvoyant and well settled in the essential nature "
"of all dharmas."

msgid "8e08512653cf4496b7dcd43053c9fbc0"
msgstr "At that time,"

msgid "a55d4455d28d48069b636de7daec8a72"
msgstr ""
"the Bhagavat thought, “To generate great swiftness, strength, impetus, and "
"stamina in the bodhisattva great beings,"

msgid "4f099c896c7744aa877951163056db9f"
msgstr "I shall give a Dharma discourse."

msgid "a8ce31607cd945939d0d7ad9fb37f5e8"
msgstr ""
"From as many world spheres as there are grains of sand in the river Ganges,"

msgid "3c3dd7761e1a4834821a744c67c4f341"
msgstr "I shall cause splendorous bodhisattva great beings to assemble."

msgid "d8f1ebad01f84dd1bd866ab6b6029f14"
msgstr ""
"Hence, I will display a sign to show that there is to be a great teaching of"
" the Dharma."

msgid "8ae7130281cd4e179389349fdf56103f"
msgstr ""
"I shall cause a great light, so that bodhisattva great beings shall come to "
"me and ask for a great Dharma teaching.”"

msgid "8b5a9cbf88bf4755bccf51706ec6a6d4"
msgstr ""
"the Bhagavat illuminated the ten directions with great clouds of light rays "
"that shone in as many worlds as there are atoms of dust in the great "
"trichiliocosm—an uncountable and inconceivable number."

msgid "bfb4f2b5b9354271a749eb8c9cb98da3"
msgstr ""
"as many bodhisattva great beings as there are atoms of dust in ten ineffable"
" quintillion buddhafields approached him from all the ten directions;"

msgid "85d142118bea4735967493139223a65e"
msgstr "present with the Bhagavat were seventy-two quintillion bodhisattvas,"

msgid "4bd7cb35d8e04506882e2893003e0339"
msgstr ""
"each and every bodhisattva great being arrived with exceptional feats beyond"
" imagination."

msgid "7a78e24f4df6492da3db2f6c1725bac8"
msgstr ""
"They first performed a fitting, inconceivable worship of the Bhagavat,"

msgid "42004f5f552b4d388ff2207c6b10e44a"
msgstr ""
"and then sat down in front of him on lotus seats that appeared through the "
"force of their aspirations."

msgid "8b08d2474d7b4d44a4dbc7b7ea357bcf"
msgstr "They stayed still, looking at the Bhagavat without blinking."

msgid "1098fbc39f1d41e7a8877070bf40ab01"
msgstr ""
"A lion throne within a great, jeweled lotus then appeared at the center of "
"the Womb of Dharmadhātu Palace. It was an uncountable number of leagues in "
"width, and of unprecedented height."

msgid "c4bed861c2b44c87a47a53305e7b1ba8"
msgstr "It was made of gems and jewels sparkling in every way,"

msgid "9bac563bdd3849c6a7d685808e424c60"
msgstr ""
"with lightning for lamps, and a surrounding railing made of gems and jewels."

msgid "04916f6d939a4ffba19942474d32bf89"
msgstr "Its staffs were of gems and jewels of inconceivable brilliance,"

msgid "288938f589524460983c6d1219f587f1"
msgstr "and incomparable gems and jewels enclosed it."

msgid "9f61e0aa56664011bb7a851f388b1e9e"
msgstr "Jewel garlands splendid beyond comparison beautified the throne,"

msgid "16bb1033f7b4434ca587f43b6a830a4e"
msgstr "studded with many types of precious gems."

msgid "a03da9a7f1e8480f83690776042832e4"
msgstr "It was hung about with raised parasols, standards, and flags."

msgid "d84cdaf1225a42518899904238f9d8f5"
msgstr ""
"From above the lion throne within the great lotus of gems and jewels, ten "
"innumerable quintillions of light rays now issued forth"

msgid "397b7b54bc7949f2ab551aee0c0a5105"
msgstr ""
"in all directions and illumined the very many world spheres in the ten "
"directions by their great brightness."

msgid "c70a8c13ba0d4df29d7805f60be82dcd"
msgstr ""
"And at that very time, from each and every one of the ten directions, gods,"

msgid "900cf17ffdec492d847ac096aae24a8f"
msgstr "nāgas,"

msgid "823d347263df4514ab7c5ae17ee02b1a"
msgstr "yakṣas,"

msgid "c98f0aad110a4511b23f5ce942662b9f"
msgstr "gandharvas,"

msgid "3dd4938484ec4d8c80b8d064cc7f0fa1"
msgstr "demigods,"

msgid "0aee760199644960bdbc94ad1172f0df"
msgstr "garuḍa,"

msgid "668f8ad7594e43b194f6b871de03c5c9"
msgstr "kinnaras,"

msgid "0199c482500f4ee397802486e6fbff98"
msgstr "great serpents,"

msgid "ee864265210f45e5ab7c40a4fb577495"
msgstr "śakras,"

msgid "1168d383771e49c3b66eece75718fc66"
msgstr "brahmās,"

msgid "10290d91866345bd8955c85030afd3d1"
msgstr ""
"and world protectors arrived, as many as there are atoms of dust in the "
"ineffable quintillion buddhafields."

msgid "d47d80c6c2cc4e5e936f4869c4f7639a"
msgstr ""
"Some of them arrived together with a quintillion apsaras, uncountable and "
"beyond conception, singing and playing musical instruments while they sat in"
" jeweled palaces."

msgid "25c94f9f68a94032b00e7329cd9205d6"
msgstr "Some arrived with palaces that were made of flowers,"

msgid "15d3dc535ee1463ebd28383f72381fc8"
msgstr "others with palaces were made of heaps of uragasāra sandalwood."

msgid "7135c56840584745825c2787d6206dfb"
msgstr "Some palaces were made of pearls, others of diamonds,"

msgid "03d54554b2ab4a9cabfb7ae83569bcac"
msgstr "and others still of gems and jewels that shone like diamonds."

msgid "b61f3f7fc7ec4bc79cdf0051625a8cec"
msgstr "Some were made of gold from the river Jāmbū,"

msgid "e6eee820ef774047a1873cb906ba30c7"
msgstr "and others were built with gems that shone in all colors."

msgid "f4e5699f2b614fd8bf6e7e3975d7bbfa"
msgstr ""
"Some were made of the vaśirāja gem and others of wish-fulfilling jewels."

msgid "f24005620e124b19b5fbec3c8d085c0e"
msgstr "Still other palaces were made of those gems worn by Śakra."

msgid "072dbf79da3a475aae1a26504be556bd"
msgstr ""
"Yet others arrived with uncountable, inconceivable quadrillions of apsaras, "
"singing and playing musical instruments while they sat in palaces of great "
"jewels, gems beaming uninterruptedly from the array of pure, ocean-ground "
"jewels."

msgid "ba9ad734ced441eda7593a4859b1978e"
msgstr ""
"As they arrived, they first worshipped the Bhagavat in an inconceivable, "
"matchless, immeasurable, and limitless manner."

msgid "4955c59468a44f6da4417e198f0141f0"
msgstr ""
"Then they arranged themselves on one side, on seats that manifested through "
"their own aspirations."

msgid "8c419bc7807d485f8a355e79b41f6163"
msgstr "they stayed still, looking at the Bhagavat without blinking."

msgid "67e8c846370b4bf98ea25c2c09406b82"
msgstr ""
"At that very moment this world sphere, a great trichiliocosm, turned into "
"Jāmbū River gold."

msgid "da2ad510639740e8b0cecb64b61fdff8"
msgstr "It was adorned with trees of many great gems and jewels,"

msgid "5f09ccf433714f2c89a43f54aa565f8a"
msgstr "divine flowering trees,"

msgid "6ba0f8bb41844d96848a783d117fe1ef"
msgstr "trees of fine fabrics,"

msgid "80602e8d30a14af7bd535cdb601980c6"
msgstr ""
"It was covered with a net of precious moon gems, sun gems, and vidyutpradīpa"
" gems."

msgid "7395a97936bb4940b1952329780feead"
msgstr "Parasols, standards, and flags were hoisted."

msgid "39402de2ea684aadb191e2539a3f9223"
msgstr ""
"nnumerable quintillions of apsaras with half their bodies in sight thronged "
"all trees, which were enveloped by strings of pearls and garlands of great "
"precious jewels."

msgid "756ab70c0c17474fad006fdd22d418f7"
msgstr ""
"At that time these verses rang out from the lion throne with its great, "
"jeweled lotus inside:"

msgid "bf17b9f68f834951bef4285cd11b40bd"
msgstr "I came about by the force of your merit."

msgid "43b8016c83ec463ca065f173b0c166cb"
msgstr "“Come, be seated, king of the best among men!"

msgid "de900f755b43442fa4d9b47fc76e594c"
msgstr "Victor, best among the two-footed."

msgid "292c49834e204025b7babebe7437a445"
msgstr "Fulfilling my wish, today I shall support you,"

msgid "00237aeb4fde4d46bae4e3ad0fe65853"
msgstr "“My body is made of jewels."

msgid "80933eca331643e283180ba362078ea4"
msgstr "Oh Guide, for your sake, At my center is a beautiful jewel lotus;"

msgid "ae59c1bef57c40aab1c7d7d28f0842e1"
msgstr "Protector, please fulfill my wish today!"

msgid "96a0d068f7294007af4b1bc277a9fefa"
msgstr "“Seated on this jewel lotus,"

msgid "3dd961203cb64b4ba1a4f528b8f062f3"
msgstr "You shall beautify this entire world and me."

msgid "eda956aa533d4678bc6c507bf2293a06"
msgstr "Hearing such Dharma, one obtains a lion throne like this!"

msgid "52d41515a67a4e9790d60674a5d39527"
msgstr "You shall teach the Dharma to many millions of living beings."

msgid "172e475888a94f1b9dbc3dc8098afeff"
msgstr ""
"“Thousands of light rays shining from your limbs Illuminate many world "
"spheres."

msgid "57f8de48256346f2967b4f7bf9f0d54a"
msgstr "This is the sign of someone in whom joy is born."

msgid "727cc1f630394b02bc334db810e96300"
msgstr "Guide, ascend to me!"

msgid "46d3fd0fd91245ac8524049c8019cef5"
msgstr ""
"In the past, in this very place, I have supported eighty million self-arisen"
" sages."

msgid "326658fdd8654dbfb80f230c8c01ce90"
msgstr "“Quickly, take your seat and grant your favor!"

msgid "cd3089007e19425782bf35aa4e7aabc6"
msgstr "May the Bhagavat also, today, bestow his favor!”"

msgid "de8501275b7347cdaaadc3e505c33c40"
msgstr "At this the Bhagavat arose from his previous seat and"

msgid "ef687980b008433d83b4fab41068ad73"
msgstr ""
"sat down on the lion throne with its great jewel lotus inside. He sat with "
"his legs crossed and observed the entire gathering of bodhisattvas."

msgid "305d4f28c4f447f980417a787f7b2873"
msgstr ""
"Then, to those bodhisattva great beings, he signaled that he was about to "
"deliver a distinguished Dharma teaching."

msgid "6e5a394e0a1342b9b9fb57ade168ec42"
msgstr ""
"At that very time, the entire assembly of bodhisattvas had the thought,"

msgid "dd348d95d2254a7abab00ebb0beec66f"
msgstr ""
"“The youthful Mañjuśrī should now inquire of the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the "
"Perfect and Complete Buddha, about non-arising and non-cessation. We have "
"not heard that Dharma teaching for a long time.”"

msgid "c8ddb8a2fa7a4ef7833cfaf7bb1697e7"
msgstr "The youthful Mañjuśrī had understood the Bhagavat’s signal,"

msgid "f981c48b899745c2b4475ded4f2968a2"
msgstr "and he also knew what the bodhisattva great beings were thinking."

msgid "15c41d98376a4e03a77c4f821c09a7df"
msgstr ""
"So he arose and adjusted his upper robe so that one shoulder was uncovered."

msgid "0363f2c958e24368b3106f9bf05c3fee"
msgstr ""
"He then knelt in front of the Bhagavat with his right knee placed in the "
"center of a lotus."

msgid "29916381d4194e8894d06c4a059257ae"
msgstr "With joined palms he then addressed this question to the Bhagavat:"

msgid "cef065258093474495ad83b7e09d916c"
msgstr "“Bhagavat, ‘non-arising’ and ‘non-cessation’ have been spoken of."

msgid "046b21b3b92642fb90d96154dd576837"
msgstr ""
"Bhagavat, to what dharma do the terms ‘non-arising’ and ‘non-cessation’ "
"refer?”"

msgid "9d5ff6144a8d4cc2922cafea8addeb2a"
msgstr "He also expressed his question in verse:"

msgid "55687d0e71484522bcda65faf3aca4f6"
msgstr "Of ‘non-cessation’ and ‘non-arising.’"

msgid "70db697b37d74b0aa28d6c8745521634"
msgstr "“Guide, you speak"

msgid "f5ee8a4b0ab14eee89e674f2d6015a00"
msgstr "Greatly wise one, How do you explain those terms?"

msgid "cbff6db5a80f4e4a9a9293fc8cecdd1a"
msgstr "“ ‘Non-cessation’ and ‘non-arising,’"

msgid "df5266bc87f54bf4b6753787c249ba60"
msgstr "Why are they called so?"

msgid "b6d9d7ba34704a06bd78017719e709f8"
msgstr "Through analogies and reasons!"

msgid "020f3c98028b4493977803f090f3e61b"
msgstr "Great sage, please tell us"

msgid "80c24ed707054204859563034b3768a6"
msgstr "“These many bodhisattvas have come here,"

msgid "b27365bfdf3c4b03b91a590915e841d0"
msgstr "Wishing for awareness; They were sent to salute you,"

msgid "b587ba00b1704e4d901d3f348ff085fb"
msgstr "by many guides of the world."

msgid "1e537020a24a4b6bba91819e8910dcd9"
msgstr "So please teach the lofty and excellent, good Dharma!”"

msgid "0baf1f286cc34b78830b79cb68f2757b"
msgstr "the Bhagavat said to the youthful Mañjuśrī:"

msgid "b202d02fd85c4fd1b6c92cd0bfe384e1"
msgstr ""
"You are striving for the benefit of many people, for the happiness of many "
"people, and with compassion for the world."

msgid "a3e43ef8b7414dbf817fc0f83073353c"
msgstr ""
"You are doing so for the goodness, benefit, and happiness of a great group "
"of beings, both gods and men."

msgid "17b7cb0dc7404967bc28185360fc09cd"
msgstr ""
"You are also acting so that the bodhisattva great beings who have come here "
"may obtain the level of a buddha."

msgid "fbf49d9055ee4639994ef64c2c26f28b"
msgstr "“Good, Mañjuśrī, good!"

msgid "89bc1b1a6a4a4735b69caeac64b97d9f"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, it is good that you think to ask the Tathāgata about this matter."

msgid "2f6bf227f0714d10bb3510c7bdf383d9"
msgstr ""
"you should apply yourself to this point without alarm, without fear, and "
"without hesitation."

msgid "f5214cef22a745e68def022cf54f6b64"
msgstr "And, Mañjuśrī, you must rely on awareness."

msgid "9d36beedbc124c4ea97c90826dc51183"
msgstr ""
"“It is as follows. Mañjuśrī, imagine that this wide earth were made entirely"
" of beryl,"

msgid "3a50306b840f43acb72378ca26fac435"
msgstr ""
"so that in that beryl one could see reflections of the abode of the Thirty-"
"Three; of Śakra, lord of the gods; and of his Palace of Victory."

msgid "74da6b06d0a4427fa68a5164ac3b3b97"
msgstr ""
"And imagine that Śakra, lord of the gods, could be seen there, playing and "
"enjoying himself with the five divine objects of pleasure."

msgid "16282db39c6a429297c39241cacc2886"
msgstr ""
"“At that time, the gods might call out to all the men, women, boys, and "
"girls of Jambūdvīpa,"

msgid "9169b7a51449460d875982744345fc34"
msgstr "‘Come here, men and women!"

msgid "a762ebb91f7d4b3fb9c573359d902e07"
msgstr ""
"Look at Śakra, lord of the gods, as he is playing, enjoying, and amusing "
"himself with the five divine objects of pleasure in his Palace of Victory."

msgid "92a1bd498fee4cb0ba6db14d286cad18"
msgstr "Come, all men and women,"

msgid "7f2df2a6cefb42ae9820f042d027a74e"
msgstr "offer gifts and make merits."

msgid "4dc00e384b6f4ab0946d9a788b774723"
msgstr "Take up discipline and abide by it."

msgid "a221a8121959422493a344a4f3dec42e"
msgstr ""
"hen you shall also get to play, enjoy, and amuse yourself in such Palaces of"
" Victory."

msgid "8546f955d6aa4723a378b3026cdae6cb"
msgstr ""
"You will become like Śakra himself and will come to possess wealth like his."
" The lord of the gods, Śakra, has all divine enjoyments, and so shall you.’"

msgid "15037d4fa7ac47248295c61cec9045f1"
msgstr ""
"“Then, Mañjuśrī, all those men, women, girls, and boys, who could see the "
"abode of the Thirty-Three along with Śakra, lord of the gods, and his Palace"
" of Victory reflected in the wide earth of beryl,"

msgid "7ca3210404ce4799852a5912a7ababd1"
msgstr ""
"would fold their hands toward this reflection. They would scatter flowers "
"and offer perfumes toward it, saying,"

msgid "e6033c8a0b634e9aab899be40f8f2b3d"
msgstr "‘May we also obtain such a body as that of Śakra, lord of the gods;"

msgid "12bfede1e4fe4429ae644dbee223f470"
msgstr ""
"may we also play, enjoy, and amuse ourselves in the Palace of Victory, just "
"like Śakra, lord of the gods.’"

msgid "131fe0fcd8f54bb5ac03a5bba93ee5a8"
msgstr ""
"“However, those beings would not understand that this would merely be a "
"reflection in the wide earth of beryl, a reflection occurring due to the "
"complete purity of the beryl, wherein the abode of the Thirty-Three, along "
"with Śakra, lord of the gods, and his Palace of Victory, could be seen."

msgid "349418b724584707a103a8b3ce4d2de0"
msgstr ""
"Wishing for the state of Śakra, they would then offer gifts and make merits."

msgid "4a44d569170549908433df459845ee84"
msgstr ""
"They would take up discipline and abide by that. They would then dedicate "
"the roots of what is wholesome toward birth in that reflection of the abode "
"of the Thirty-Three."

msgid "dd542f0924584a9e9ebe52706913fb74"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, in that wide earth of beryl there would, of course, be no abode "
"of the Thirty-Three, and neither would there be a Palace of Victory, or "
"Śakra, lord of the gods."

msgid "1b3807a1b5184b6686ad8b54c015ec3d"
msgstr "However, due to the purity of the great beryl,"

msgid "ec8940d8d69a4318b6ff288695ad7afd"
msgstr ""
"the abode of the Thirty-Three along with the Palace of Victory and Śakra, "
"lord of the gods would all be visible."

msgid "f43de92020084b30aeb8f296a27957d6"
msgstr ""
"Non-existent, non-arisen, and non-ceased, their reflections would be seen "
"because of the purity of the great beryl."

msgid "6b48cc7eb8d04b359c8591719a641a08"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, Mañjuśrī, it is due to the complete purity of the mind, as"
" well as due to proper cultivation, that sentient beings see the body of a "
"tathāgata."

msgid "b2b23de9dd0d469bbb3ae127c230cf93"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, it is due to the power of the Tathāgata that sentient beings see "
"him."

msgid "f008d3d9897b4690852e23bdc1384e6b"
msgstr "And still he remains non-existent, non-arisen, and non-ceased."

msgid "e86c159a6f43455e8f63ea193aa6c654"
msgstr "He is neither existence nor non-existence,"

msgid "f3b79115bc014505a968799458347cce"
msgstr "neither visible nor invisible,"

msgid "37aaa71b143346bb91d686f219fb8b34"
msgstr "neither worldly nor unworldly,"

msgid "aa7404522b0746b69fd5c426249fac00"
msgstr "neither an object of thinking nor not an object of thinking,"

msgid "133e25ab88444ac4b92cac27ee3ae42e"
msgstr "neither existent nor non-existent."

msgid "5d900b3a69834581b6f6f1e7615ad086"
msgstr ""
"“It is so, Mañjuśrī, that sentient beings focus on the reflection of the "
"Tathāgata"

msgid "ad056b9d078a47dc93c288a804cb95c4"
msgstr ""
"and offer it flowers, perfumes, garments, and jewels while making this "
"aspiration:"

msgid "282cde9bb1cb4a56ba2ceb078624f4d4"
msgstr ""
"‘May we also become like the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and Complete "
"Buddha.’"

msgid "2abc533089cf46a2906b3e9931975ed1"
msgstr "Wishing for a buddha’s awareness,"

msgid "d88510c2ba95458d8e4fb9687313d419"
msgstr "they offer gifts and make merit."

msgid "7a1ba9570676467b828774d10264ce3c"
msgstr "They take up discipline and abide by it."

msgid "65400b76c32243008ddf8a870e18c3be"
msgstr ""
"Then they dedicate that root of what is wholesome toward obtaining a "
"tathāgata’s awareness."

msgid "ae7705b9f9fa45b9a4e4117175eafb00"
msgstr "“It is as follows: Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "787ba89c24284e539dfa1695bb7fbcba"
msgstr ""
"the reflection of Śakra, ruler of the gods, on that wide earth made of beryl"
" does not move."

msgid "a87b512d717d4c0f859083409125c67f"
msgstr "Nor does he think, elaborate, construct, or conceptualize."

msgid "495c1abdd08e4513a880cc93826a601e"
msgstr ""
"It is not a construct, not a concept, inconceivable, and not a mental "
"placement."

msgid "c253dd0f7562439bad951635ab4cab1f"
msgstr "He is peaceful and cool, non-arising and non-cessation,"

msgid "dd2fe5dd04054fbc9e71e30fa5509fd6"
msgstr "not seen, not heard, not smelt, not tasted, not touched,"

msgid "c5906a1afbc8492693bdc8dd98d09fb8"
msgstr ""
"not a sign, not a cognition, and not something that can be made known."

msgid "c23565b86b014955a0bd3741de93d4bb"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and "
"Complete Buddha does not move."

msgid "613aed61bc954144a3b2ef9417668691"
msgstr ""
"He is not a construct, not a concept, inconceivable, not a mental placement."

msgid "74079836686340c683854ae389728f10"
msgstr "“Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata is in the realm of non-arising."

msgid "6b39e29fe05f4861a09f4e3b48963c6c"
msgstr "On the other hand, he appears in the world as a reflected image."

msgid "ae93f359748b44dea5e01403bfd4466b"
msgstr ""
"According to the beliefs of sentient beings he displays diverse appearances "
"and diverse lifespans."

msgid "b1f70930b2df4ee39c2ce9ec5a08c636"
msgstr ""
"He appears among sentient beings who have become fitting receptacles for "
"awakening thanks to their maturation and belief."

msgid "b3b8553e52c342309d30edae0040d1a7"
msgstr ""
"These sentient beings then hear the Dharma according to their dispositions "
"and beliefs."

msgid "5ea7a93d794c4c608e7cf46da036b980"
msgstr "According to their dispositions they understand the three vehicles"

msgid "5fce6dd53c3347589b86d888bc32f04c"
msgstr "“It is as follows: Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "ccfd9b863b3b407baa043a7a38ee670a"
msgstr ""
"a great Dharma drum for making sounds of Dharma, which come about through "
"the force of merit of the gods of the Thirty-Three,"

msgid "54978e6da6fa4f1aa7455b70529aacbb"
msgstr "is placed in the atmosphere above the Vaijayanta Palace,"

msgid "6cea04c4705a4fad9404dd92d376ded0"
msgstr "beyond visible range. The divine scions cannot see it or behold it."

msgid "58aba29b934742e091755fc7933ba151"
msgstr "“However, Mañjuśrī, it is a great Dharma drum."

msgid "9cd1f1a2493c4f4ea0da80bf3d616e9d"
msgstr ""
"Sometimes the gods in the heaven of the Thirty-Three become so intensely and"
" continuously oblivious from playing with, enjoying, and delighting "
"themselves with their divine pleasures"

msgid "88776daf0656450a8322b7627702bee2"
msgstr ""
"that they fail to enter the divine hall called Sudharma to jointly chant the"
" Dharma."

msgid "f393b2cbdd0f4e2d994bfa3526c1a785"
msgstr ""
"And, Mañjuśrī, Śakra, lord of the gods, becomes so intensely and "
"continuously oblivious from playing with, enjoying, and delighting himself "
"with his divine pleasures"

msgid "d9f728c702fe4718b1d3e7511ce2d810"
msgstr "that he fails to sit on his Dharma seat to speak of the Dharma."

msgid "078c1da879364907b8cf239655196348"
msgstr "“Mañjuśrī, at such times, that great Dharma drum,"

msgid "b783009bf2fd47cc88bf2de6c5501879"
msgstr ""
"not to be seen or beheld, hanging in the atmosphere beyond visible range,"

msgid "bb120b474c414ac3b92675a6913cd233"
msgstr ""
"plays a Dharma sound that addresses all the gods in the heaven of the "
"Thirty-Three,"

msgid "c000eb57cf7940ed85a319ebc0ae5376"
msgstr "‘Friends! Form, sound, smell, flavor, and touch are impermanent;"

msgid "29cd652af66b418c8402c131b31197bb"
msgstr "do not be careless."

msgid "8f846924b00542e78f6dbf1d661fd909"
msgstr "Do not quickly fall down from this abode!"

msgid "a9089ce049234cb78f25299e0a0547fa"
msgstr "Friends, all co-producing factors are suffering!"

msgid "fd88a70814334c4db2918ad0883ebb8a"
msgstr "Friends, all co-producing factors are empty!"

msgid "c842252cd1b543bcbf0a59c1ffac1ebe"
msgstr "Friends, all co-producing factors are without self!"

msgid "e894e514611e496ab95413a0f7ded826"
msgstr ""
"for those who die and fall from here, to take birth here once again is "
"difficult."

msgid "e41c94a6ebd04933ad0782ac51a7cba2"
msgstr "Do not become careless:"

msgid "da4a29b8a9c54cb3b1c3b8f360319dcf"
msgstr "delight in the pleasant joy of Dharma."

msgid "8b6714cd788e4c438690f2d6a5101be5"
msgstr "being inclined toward the Dharma,"

msgid "cc19ce46314b4debbba6d380c3c92959"
msgstr ""
"with Dharma pouring like rain, recollecting and placing the Dharma in the "
"mind."

msgid "ac007036c75a495eb6c857ac84fbc286"
msgstr ""
"You shall not then have to part from these divine enjoyments and delights in"
" games of pleasure.’"

msgid "2b2aeadcea3246f59379d4431063c48b"
msgstr "“At that time, Mañjuśrī, due to the sound of that great Dharma drum—"

msgid "1fb865c84814401d91dc220c9f159360"
msgstr "invisible, formless, inconceivable, not a mental construct,"

msgid "25d31ba596274ad6ba542d9d734117d9"
msgstr "out of sight,"

msgid "0c3b036b366e44dd90a53a696cbfadcc"
msgstr "unborn, unceasing, beyond the way of words,"

msgid "f9ea6cf315c44a1fa4ae41a6c3d2f7c4"
msgstr "and devoid of mind, mentality, and consciousness"

msgid "b67ea66f6d26421ea1255b2e34228918"
msgstr ""
"—all the gods in the heaven of the Thirty-Three are roused, scared, alarmed,"
" and very distressed."

msgid "d35008fe541e4e17b297519b93041cfd"
msgstr "They enter the divine hall called Sudharma"

msgid "bb2bfcb679184c3ab14f90d47308b989"
msgstr "delighting in the pleasant joy of Dharma."

msgid "1ee4cff502d548198499d5ecf59a2684"
msgstr "They make the Dharma their essence,"

msgid "c6a738c411ea4872bc26ab261973a8bf"
msgstr "they become inclined toward the Dharma,"

msgid "c364224f7926448fb76479cb1db6ba38"
msgstr "recollecting and keeping the Dharma in mind."

msgid "2680b38ecbb94b47af8aa27e1ad63382"
msgstr ""
"When they die and fall from that abode, they will again reach excellent "
"places."

msgid "22a008e6c38342a2b97cefa3a90b6c47"
msgstr "Śakra, the king of the gods, then enters Sudharma, the divine hall,"

msgid "7ed5f15c69ec414ea3431c523f0b74a6"
msgstr "takes a seat on the Dharma throne, and teaches the Dharma."

msgid "1d1a405e49014c2ebf9f44808b4f4edb"
msgstr "“Mañjuśrī, when the demigods battle against the gods,"

msgid "1a0124449c8d45a29811c4e46bf4aea8"
msgstr ""
"whenever the gods of the heaven of the Thirty-Three are being defeated,"

msgid "4cea5cac34d74fad8587b1a04faec385"
msgstr ""
"the Dharma drum emits a sound that makes the demigods so frightened, "
"alarmed, agitated, and distressed that they flee."

msgid "ce676f8292a545099091c8cab6e165d6"
msgstr ""
"Nevertheless, Mañjuśrī, that great Dharma drum does not have a producer,"

msgid "e57240dba9f746d291275d6fa4a29284"
msgstr "nor does it have a body."

msgid "5fd199f02dcd497a80f604b6b9bb683d"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, that Dharma drum is invisible,"

msgid "6a3a4160c2924d8696627122fc2f5c37"
msgstr "not to be beheld, not true,"

msgid "b466347995124b8cb666e50820e3e8a7"
msgstr "not real, with no mind, without intention,"

msgid "779d1564f41344258b82d50c36191c77"
msgstr "sign-less,"

msgid "f1bb9ec5ab754ab2bf5920901f642ec5"
msgstr "voiceless,"

msgid "dc59f6ff8250407a9eaf8fab866d1cd9"
msgstr "immaterial,"

msgid "3730d755f66348908761c1fe416d6b7c"
msgstr "non-dual,"

msgid "867405dc6d324ad59bc83c663aca6f6b"
msgstr "and out of sight."

msgid "a71f9a62e8514cf196a5966e39d8196b"
msgstr ""
"“Nevertheless, Mañjuśrī, for those gods in the heaven of the Thirty-Three "
"who have previously purified themselves,"

msgid "1384080d119240efbc02d58a07e93675"
msgstr "a sound comes forth from the great Dharma drum."

msgid "e17f11710a3b48228875dc0a4438b4c3"
msgstr ""
"It occurs to pacify all the misfortunes, troubles, and afflictions of the "
"gods of the Thirty-Three."

msgid "e23fc30039574dca81150b87286f18c0"
msgstr "“Mañjuśrī, in the same way that from that great Dharma drum,"

msgid "65ab448018fe4692b0645f1782c9f69c"
msgstr "invisible,"

msgid "d592fce41f684f3d8dd69d6b561a7238"
msgstr "not to be beheld,"

msgid "88a56174c1284311b8af1f3cb108adb2"
msgstr "not true, not real, with no mind, without intention,"

msgid "f109b9844fce44999583c342554874f7"
msgstr "sign-less,"

msgid "bd0e921e3dcd416399539dce259f5c10"
msgstr "formless,"

msgid "5acc119cd29543d0afb7d86af329a331"
msgstr "voiceless, immaterial,"

msgid "af0d8895469644b3ac928558d16fbf1d"
msgstr "non-dual,"

msgid "5cffa2b9c3fa41f58b9ce1bcd12bf9c8"
msgstr "and out of sight"

msgid "ebe395714f084becb7cde23ee3d4b09d"
msgstr ""
"that sound of Dharma occurs to pacify all the misfortunes, troubles, and "
"afflictions of the gods of the Thirty-Three,"

msgid "47421213928f444f9dec701b8343e19b"
msgstr ""
"so, too, Mañjuśrī, although the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and "
"Complete Buddha is invisible,"

msgid "86c0600717684045962893cd482b17fa"
msgstr "not true, not real,"

msgid "d6d6df156d234c929814e7343ec9423b"
msgstr "with no mind, without intention,"

msgid "35ba74b2583c457883a86b80f8a81936"
msgstr "and out of sight, nevertheless,"

msgid "7afd7571b95d43e2b18ce3c49b5ecd54"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, sentient beings perceive the voice of Dharma due to the maturation"
" of previous karma, according to their individual aspirations and interests."

msgid "55ba21fc4c634a659370bca5864f2fa9"
msgstr ""
"And that sound of Dharma occurs to pacify all misfortunes, troubles, and "
"afflictions of all sentient beings."

msgid "ed4997b5ab1d4202bc2e34cb5a84b6f5"
msgstr ""
"Being the voice of Dharma, it is regarded in the world as the voice of the "
"Tathāgata."

msgid "ac8cb45b56bd4dfc9104ac960b8f5971"
msgstr "“Mañjuśrī, there is no Tathāgata."

msgid "df45b4ac4aad4177aaf041dfee06cc22"
msgstr ""
"However, the designation ‘Tathāgata’ comes about in the world because of the"
" voice of Dharma."

msgid "1671916b2463454b93e18ccb5fff67ac"
msgstr ""
"It is exclusively due to the maturation of sentient beings’ previous "
"wholesome karma"

msgid "d70f7432742e4a0bb5839693abe4dc42"
msgstr "that they perceive the voice of the Tathāgata."

msgid "8584b675d7af46de996f8a63634a8a8a"
msgstr ""
"That voice emerges in order to produce happiness for all sentient beings and"
" to prompt those who are careless."

msgid "d75d2372a588473a8d86064a773c50ff"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, as those sentient beings hear that sound,"

msgid "7986f009ac2943a2a42a5e7aa83919bc"
msgstr ""
"they form the concept of a tathāgata, thinking, ‘This is the Tathāgata’s "
"body.’"

msgid "eec8b57b46304383b3046ad52b3e50fa"
msgstr ""
"“The speech of the Tathāgata is heard so that beginner bodhisattvas and all "
"immature, ordinary people may generate roots of what is wholesome by taking "
"the Tathāgata as their reference point."

msgid "45fa5f7863c34d11aeb230ea0159cb43"
msgstr ""
"However, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata should be known to be non-arisen and non-"
"ceasing."

msgid "8480aa426e0b464f9c742a43d77948d1"
msgstr "“It is as follows: Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "0dcf702db544476780eb231a857a8c47"
msgstr "at the end of summertime, during the first month of rains,"

msgid "2e402541fd97486abcb17924a04fe20f"
msgstr "due to the maturation of sentient beings’ previous karma,"

msgid "1cf258d199f24131b94d3a9b2daa8cde"
msgstr ""
"and to generate, out of the multitudes of seeds and elements, all the grass,"
" thickets, medicinal herbs, and trees on earth,"

msgid "7ace88209710405eb99f34a0d73b888a"
msgstr "winds begin to blow in the atmosphere and the sky above;"

msgid "cf0920b20d214d6490b8ac983b8aa5b0"
msgstr ""
"then water comes about due to that wind, and it falls on the great earth."

msgid "8b9510f69e2b4d35af29e4a15fa8ef91"
msgstr "Thus, the great earth is satisfied,"

msgid "293db7cc4d394d06ba1e770aeda50ee6"
msgstr "and all sentient beings in Jambūdvīpa are joyful and happy."

msgid "123bf4c5bea446d49171f0b8f892972e"
msgstr "Referring to this, the notion of a ‘cloud’ comes about in the world."

msgid "331851a13a744778af415d2a9310ba22"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, whenever not much rain falls from the atmosphere and the sky "
"above,"

msgid "1f06849cefbc4a498a9da25986ec5f1d"
msgstr ""
"all the sentient beings in Jambūdvīpa think, ‘Here there is not a cloud.’"

msgid "4f219acfbdb54e6a8336eff4d366b737"
msgstr ""
"But when, Mañjuśrī, a lot of rain falls on the great earth from the "
"atmosphere and the sky above,"

msgid "b9de6413eaee41c98f1c1bd3e943a695"
msgstr "they say: ‘Oh, a great cloud is pouring down water,"

msgid "3947e360635442e1b004b3410ba2fa2d"
msgstr "satisfying the great earth.’"

msgid "0d522b698aed4d03806ba9f5572ebf1c"
msgstr ""
"“However, Mañjuśrī, when this happens there is neither a cloud, nor anything"
" that can be designated as a cloud."

msgid "797e7acdd4924958941d6bf5ca7e32c7"
msgstr ""
"a large mass of water is generated by the wind, and then it falls from the "
"atmosphere above."

msgid "5e376d674b044e44ae7c48a7d571ec4a"
msgstr "disappears in the atmosphere itself,"

msgid "49d5444f06224ed28be7377b961f6fbf"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, that cumulus of water above in the atmosphere, stirred by the "
"wind and releasing water, is designated a cloud due to the maturation of "
"sentient beings’ previous karma."

msgid "660562242f5d46f0b0a2a126532f9470"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, no cloud can be found there,"

msgid "6309d86909cb47e6b363f5fc9c457e5f"
msgstr "nor anything that could be designated a cloud."

msgid "74dd093d8ef644a7a0acbf00714c80be"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, the cloud is non-arisen and non-ceasing;"

msgid "91c2fd375554469e9e1a3917371fcfec"
msgstr ""
"it does not enter the way of mind, and it is free from coming and going."

msgid "e59877262176415d9538b792c2cc632d"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, Mañjuśrī, for bodhisattva great beings who have "
"accumulated previous roots of what is wholesome;"

msgid "09a05bd20f6a4e3c947cc1da1f5bf231"
msgstr ""
"for other sentient beings who wish for the awareness of a hearer or a "
"pratyekabuddha;"

msgid "4b4a8e6546144c39a0da7abe40d61b87"
msgstr ""
"and for those sentient beings who have accumulated roots of what is "
"wholesome and possess the causes to be shown the path to nirvāṇa,"

msgid "84aa34c06c0c48c793881467f23da121"
msgstr ""
"the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and Complete Buddha with unobstructed "
"brilliance comes to be counted as arisen in the world."

msgid "e849bbd16903461b9130459715c73c86"
msgstr ""
"“Whatever he says is thus (tathā), undistorted, thus and not otherwise. "
"Therefore,"

msgid "19fc2862c95947389cd0cb0a6f0f9e36"
msgstr "he was given the name Tathāgata among gods and men."

msgid "f3463f2e535945d69c78019b80b2f9b4"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, this word appears among gods and men: Tathāgata."

msgid "a3a06d63db474caba1483e72e8149d71"
msgstr "However, Mañjuśrī, there is no Tathāgata to be found."

msgid "318bae1513c24445b7705b3a1caeb353"
msgstr "The Tathāgata, Mañjuśrī, is not a sign,"

msgid "dbb9d7047958452084ce427e0eef75d3"
msgstr "and he is free from signs."

msgid "731c5e3a335c4ec1a72d8c34ebf48556"
msgstr "He is unreal, non-arisen, and non-ceasing."

msgid "5943c99e81bd44d59c497a4c044b69ff"
msgstr ""
"“On the other hand, Mañjuśrī, the appearance of the Tathāgata satisfies and "
"entertains this world, including the gods,"

msgid "86448afefcf34c279c2cac9ba7d0490c"
msgstr ""
"And then, due to the ripening of previous karma of beginner bodhisattvas and"
" immature, ordinary people who are guided by means of nirvāṇa,"

msgid "c756d7eb803743b2a015a8f2ed9c027c"
msgstr "They think, ‘The Tathāgata has passed into complete nirvāṇa.’"

msgid "41365e32940348829011d1cca3a6ecc2"
msgstr "However, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata neither arises nor ceases."

msgid "da3a128fd0e94cdabed96deeb9b46f67"
msgstr "The Tathāgata, Mañjuśrī, is non-arisen and non-ceasing."

msgid "eea27c475f6349b78dccb16d15345feb"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, when some water is taken as a point of reference for an unreal "
"cloud"

msgid "a2d5a346397642ed9807959a1b34d7af"
msgstr "that has not arisen nor ceased, and is non-existent,"

msgid "6fcf25162b194b2ca526d3a6576cbdd5"
msgstr ""
"the designation ‘cloud’ is established in the world. In the very same way,"

msgid "45733f27c80746a8bf91376b56761507"
msgstr "“It is as follows: Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "0dd0481ff92d4b3b9da0b7ab44273dfd"
msgstr ""
"every day the great and unsurpassed Brahmā, who controls ten trichiliocosms,"
" looks upon all the classes of gods, as far as the class of the gods of the "
"Four Great Kings."

msgid "c33595616cda49c9975b13f19cf8afab"
msgstr ""
"At that time, Mañjuśrī, while the great Brahmā, who controls ten "
"trichiliocosms, looks upon all the classes of gods,"

msgid "3583a4171d9548fda278d46fd6c06db1"
msgstr "they all abandon their games of pleasure, delights, and enjoyments."

msgid "0ce65e76c52f49ed98379042e7ce0692"
msgstr "they respectfully fold their hands"

msgid "402ebd3d289d43ec8777189531ea115c"
msgstr "and look toward the great Brahmā without blinking."

msgid "95bb53099e4a459fa7a3465cb6ecf8ba"
msgstr ""
"For a moment, the great Brahmā offers sight of himself to all the classes of"
" gods."

msgid "ebd8986fdc224c6bbe98a26f714e310d"
msgstr ""
"At that time, the gods all long to be born in the world of the great Brahmā,"

msgid "a91d1e605e02463eb77770d71a83d317"
msgstr ""
"and they dedicate their roots of what is wholesome toward taking birth in "
"the world of the great Brahmā."

msgid "d357c30938e64b04be719c4b6a3f609d"
msgstr ""
"“Moreover, Mañjuśrī, that great Brahmā, without falling down from that "
"Brahmā Palace,"

msgid "46df63f68f874a04a4d4f88dcf62b47b"
msgstr ""
"thanks to the power of his previous aspirations and due to the prior "
"accumulation of virtue on the part of the gods."

msgid "8dcdf57c29864dd7ab9ea4ed63825c47"
msgstr ""
"empowers another great Brahmā as the controller of ten trichiliocosms,"

msgid "3d256456422b41fbadc8517a66560762"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, that emanated great Brahmā looks upon all the classes of gods, as"
" far as the class of the gods of the Four Great Kings."

msgid "6250a33492984a75b595ea78a289f1f2"
msgstr "At that time, Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "3a691952ae06410ea46761e758159541"
msgstr ""
"among all the classes of gods, all the scions of the gods abandon their "
"games of pleasure, delights, and enjoyments."

msgid "b82e8ba0d6cf4bff9f06eb13f120d17b"
msgstr ""
"They stop playing their percussion instruments and halt their singing."

msgid "0420e7a836724d178bc3b03719e150e6"
msgstr "Shifting their attention from their games of pleasure and delights,"

msgid "f5c203cde23b46049d4e6a77b263876a"
msgstr ""
"they respectfully fold their hands and look toward the great Brahmā without "
"blinking."

msgid "9dff43e3af3b43929510de5154d8961b"
msgstr ""
"At that time, the gods all long to be born in the world of the great Brahmā,"
" and they dedicate their roots of what is wholesome toward taking birth in "
"the world of the great Brahmā."

msgid "9b9478247df2464c8c71809a572ced0b"
msgstr "“Still, Mañjuśrī, no Brahmā is there to be found."

msgid "fb14a7dd85ef4fb6ad3d175f682ff6d7"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, Brahmā is empty, dependent,"

msgid "64a10791c57b457c8cdd1410b593cb37"
msgstr "unreal, without syllables,"

msgid "3d65bed2e5894efa84ee33bb88354893"
msgstr "without voice, without place,"

msgid "b9fdb2e997a44b29b1fbdba8b498cb8a"
msgstr "and also not an existent thing. He is inconceivable,"

msgid "2fb4f45a46c54c6ba27d5e68630eac32"
msgstr "without signs, and free from mentality, mind, and consciousness."

msgid "8dde62f33d4f4738b23723ea864e5f18"
msgstr "He is non-arisen and unceasing."

msgid "4a79f7a8b08042acab7b27c06e6d2b79"
msgstr ""
"And yet, Mañjuśrī, a semblance of him offering sight of himself appears "
"among all the classes of gods, by the power of his own previous roots of "
"what is wholesome and aspirations, and due to the previous accumulations of "
"roots of what is wholesome on the part of those gods."

msgid "b1e3efd0cea54d99bb3e67ab08d91d83"
msgstr ""
"“Yet, Mañjuśrī, those gods do not think, ‘This Brahmā is an emanation."

msgid "e3118626df5944f2a14e804690008417"
msgstr "empty, dependent,"

msgid "5898f1af80504466a18ec1a78285c4be"
msgstr "unreal, without syllables,"

msgid "337c2aa226a34782890a27085ed16376"
msgstr "without voice, without place,"

msgid "280cd7089ca042e78c57fd55b1c1b2c1"
msgstr "not an existent thing."

msgid "373d7e28238040a2882e302addd35dba"
msgstr "and free from mentality, mind, and consciousness."

msgid "d38bc94633b44fc18289e8663d091ff2"
msgstr "He is non-arisen and unceasing.’"

msgid "eb0188e6b59a4ada87d8e9af810f2ba1"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, in the same manner the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and "
"Complete Buddha is empty,"

msgid "77f15223d9174235ba63330ec9218464"
msgstr ""
"dependent, unreal, without syllables, without voice, without place, and also"
" not an existent thing."

msgid "0d3e068058f5438cb106f8b4f382faa9"
msgstr ""
"He is inconceivable, without signs, and free from mentality, mind, and "
"consciousness."

msgid "13c4c1333d0848dd8c40dba500c8bdcd"
msgstr ""
"This is due to the power of his previous aspirations during his practice as "
"a bodhisattva, and also due to the power of all the roots of what is "
"wholesome of the beginner bodhisattvas, of those who set out on the vehicles"
" of the hearers and the pratyekabuddhas, as well as of all the immature, "
"ordinary people."

msgid "1ebc8a5c1a6e4d97a63bd6cce3537450"
msgstr ""
"He is seen in the world as a tathāgata adorned with hundreds of thousands of"
" marks, like a reflected image; and he does not move from his place."

msgid "035bd112af594eb49f26e698ba7e79e0"
msgstr ""
"“Yet, Mañjuśrī, from the body of the Tathāgata, adorned with hundreds of "
"thousands of marks, during all the empty postures of a tathāgata,"

msgid "3e6a75603695429d8733de9f388ea675"
msgstr ""
"a great Dharma teaching emanates for the sake of varied sentient beings with"
" diverse beliefs."

msgid "558fb7c71d334a23b16862b41360f60a"
msgstr ""
"“That Dharma teaching occurs to pacify all the troubles, harms, and "
"afflictions of all sentient beings."

msgid "8a155c0707a7434a99ce20e6bc5de0a6"
msgstr ""
"In that regard, the Tathāgata is the same, neutral, without concepts, and "
"does not make any distinctions."

msgid "cbe2750ee1714bb8ba3a1add3226d3cb"
msgstr ""
"Thus, Mañjuśrī, through this explanation you should understand that ‘non-"
"arising and non-cessation’ is an appellation of the Tathāgata.”"

msgid "cc9008bc1c004c84ba59d252cdbc3522"
msgstr "Then, at that time, the Bhagavat spoke the following two stanzas:"

msgid "68731a92a0894baeada0a58d596fcd3c"
msgstr "“The Tathāgata always has the quality of non-arising,"

msgid "42ac68605422430e8f67a86401451201"
msgstr "And all dharmas resemble the Sugata."

msgid "0515b2cf581e445484976e7aa563d87e"
msgstr "Yet immature minds, by their grasping at signs,"

msgid "28fad9d5ae3c4a429de6031f92116748"
msgstr "Roam the world among non-existent dharmas."

msgid "1778d01994cb49e584c1e81f8762b675"
msgstr "“The Tathāgata is a reflected image"

msgid "c70e095dd9a043ce8a8bea6404c39f2b"
msgstr "Of the wholesome Dharma without ."

msgid "e984cb8bf6ae450b9cf01ee2da2ab7a6"
msgstr "Yet here there is no tathatā and no Tathāgata,"

msgid "6b3837ae1bcb4730a448f2e28240bd9d"
msgstr "While an image is seen in the entire world."

msgid "d4b982b4a06f42839210f856467c04c0"
msgstr "“It is as follows: Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "767d29e56cb34542a1252b47f921ed03"
msgstr ""
"here in Jambūdvīpa the rays of the sun only shine at first on the great king"
" of mighty mountains."

msgid "a854d8156fee484f954469efd11e577f"
msgstr "After that, they shine on the Cakravāḍa and Mahācakravāḍa ranges."

msgid "ca4674ed815046cf974cce5650fb101c"
msgstr "After that, they shine on the elevated regions of the earth."

msgid "5b89ab09a9c54ae18beb5b7a44043406"
msgstr ""
"After that, they shine on the low-lying regions of the earth here in "
"Jambūdvīpa."

msgid "d4231c1bc45e4666951dac1a1c26be76"
msgstr ""
"“Yet those sun rays, Mañjuśrī, do not form mental constructs or concepts."

msgid "d8d2028fa8b547948d461d88b82529c7"
msgstr "They do not think or ponder."

msgid "afa794bec12c4bee8f3f60af9ef9ffb9"
msgstr ""
"The rays of the sun, Mañjuśrī, are free from mentality, mind, and "
"consciousness;"

msgid "e0e06ef061a7418b9fa4a55941c77dfe"
msgstr ""
"they are unborn and unceasing, without characteristics, free from "
"characteristics;"

msgid "8a893d23833e4bc6882c46b732b5e7fe"
msgstr "without mental placement, free from mental placement,"

msgid "09ef3a78d3b74ec6ac8d481051e6724e"
msgstr "without elaboration, free from elaboration;"

msgid "c3c231e366214a59bc92fb935aa2f084"
msgstr "without torment, free from torment;"

msgid "c1c59ff04f8a4d5597edd160da692026"
msgstr "not abiding hither, not abiding thither;"

msgid "6d69ebace5fc464093ed883d0701aa06"
msgstr "not high, not low;"

msgid "1430432515e6449892191e8fd4a26d4c"
msgstr "not bound, not liberated;"

msgid "46e5417e8562402eb2fd39b1a9eec9a3"
msgstr "not knowing, not ignorant;"

msgid "8723f0114af44a2b8cb9727a42fc69ff"
msgstr "not afflictions, not free from afflictions;"

msgid "438a1ed0ddd4455fae5969b6d4e6f412"
msgstr "not speaking the truth, not speaking falsely;"

msgid "f6359b1be413480fac1795dac699b914"
msgstr "not over there, not here;"

msgid "1febb883da8744eab44fb19ba2966f88"
msgstr "not on dry land, not in the stream;"

msgid "f812ee9c0dc64384b25cd78c39aec1ca"
msgstr "not the domain of reasoning, not the domain of non-reasoning;"

msgid "aac3d90027c04e20af2face6e738ba90"
msgstr "neither with form, nor formless."

msgid "d48432d3ee4d4847911758a7148a6849"
msgstr ""
"Yet, Mañjuśrī, due to the distinction of higher, middling, and lower places "
"on the earth,"

msgid "1c520a316128415abb9927cfbb5db412"
msgstr ""
"the light shines differently, at higher, middling, and lower degrees causing"
" varied shades."

msgid "80dc5aaa46354067ac67156c3a98c3d3"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and "
"Complete Buddha does not form mental constructs or concepts."

msgid "69fe4544cf8749318b9c2895e198abc2"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata is free from mind, mentality, and consciousness."

msgid "1913f414c8964bd6bc1305af97df712b"
msgstr "not speaking the truth, not speaking falsely;"

msgid "2a292f69f4b341a2ac60772bd1f84348"
msgstr "not on the shore, nor on the non-shore;"

msgid "4368c907dd094d44892c04531822fd4b"
msgstr "“He is not omniscient, not non-omniscient;"

msgid "37e502228b34436eb5fcf190ec0da378"
msgstr "not reasoning, not non-reasoning;"

msgid "43754f0d7a5a48ae810f2ebe4e85feb7"
msgstr "not acting, not non-acting;"

msgid "69be631199a04f57b4d8dba778951a88"
msgstr "neither mindful nor unmindful,"

msgid "e9e0e4b6a20640a4a486c7741ace7cb9"
msgstr "neither with intention nor free from intention;"

msgid "0891f351161d42b4a11eb1dad16d9701"
msgstr "neither mind nor without mind;"

msgid "57b0c6f04a0945909b53a3c05ee5e822"
msgstr "neither originated nor unoriginated;"

msgid "7edb37d67f0943d88376df9d6dbd8481"
msgstr "neither name nor no name;"

msgid "99b2502bebed4f698c76129126c96494"
msgstr "neither form nor no form;"

msgid "16fac88d606247f3b4ef434fe8e2b234"
msgstr "neither verbal expression nor non-verbal expression;"

msgid "ca86188d41314250b3484ef5d229ba4f"
msgstr ""
"neither a possible object of imputation, nor not a possible object of "
"imputation;"

msgid "dda96da4ee72402d91cb5b126745d4c4"
msgstr "neither visible nor invisible;"

msgid "c340b729b4e34511a13460dc7934f2ce"
msgstr "neither a conducive way nor not a conducive way;"

msgid "1e4a2b8139ca4f54bdec019c25648af6"
msgstr "neither leading along the way, nor not leading along the way;"

msgid "759f5285b35f4ef6a5d0020db5a2de22"
msgstr ""
"neither having obtained the result, nor not having obtained the result;"

msgid "588f32da7e7b4f7aa22e937d57ae629e"
msgstr "neither a concept, nor not a concept;"

msgid "8fe6318d913d4e8e9a68bffc43155955"
msgstr "neither free from concepts, nor not free from concepts."

msgid "578e1c04dc144aad995a379c16a50142"
msgstr ""
"“Similarly, Mañjuśrī, the rays of awareness from the round sun of the "
"Tathāgata shine brilliantly in the three realms, unimpeded throughout the "
"dharmadhātu with neither edge nor center."

msgid "71913b18d8ba43f99f1775ecd8509bee"
msgstr ""
"Once they shine, they first descend upon the bodies of bodhisattvas, whose "
"aspirations are like the great lord of mountains."

msgid "107f57654cdf4fad8b2025b60632a477"
msgstr ""
"After that, they descend upon the bodies of those who set forth on the "
"Vehicle of Pratyekabuddhas."

msgid "710b67b28ee3414c8321520b49062ef0"
msgstr ""
"Then they descend upon the bodies of those who have set forth on the "
"Hearers’ Vehicle."

msgid "4bb68e5d0f144b098dc7eb733b99088a"
msgstr ""
"After that, they descend upon the body of sentient beings with wholesome "
"aspirations, according to their specific inclinations."

msgid "e1ef7bdedfd04a3590982d59191dbf0a"
msgstr ""
"After that, the rays of awareness from the round sun of the Tathāgata even "
"descend upon the body of those sentient beings with mental continua that are"
" stuck in what is wrong."

msgid "cfc796fc02214e81b33bda76bb421867"
msgstr ""
"The rays assist all these beings by producing causes for what will come "
"later, and increase their wholesome dharmas."

msgid "f8b185f5022e40a1a365b11652867a25"
msgstr ""
"“In that respect, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata is everywhere the same, neutral, "
"without concepts, and does not make any distinctions."

msgid "5a534b061d534dfea42933385cc88591"
msgstr ""
"Moreover, Mañjuśrī, the round sun of the Tathāgata’s awareness does not "
"think, ‘I will teach this person the vast Dharma,"

msgid "39df785d6bfd47d695e394d0a3813330"
msgstr "but I will not teach that one.’ Neither do they have the concept"

msgid "05a3dd00aa0e42049f180dff14319d89"
msgstr "‘This person has vast beliefs"

msgid "797fb7e2540d460fa56e312142ab9bab"
msgstr "that one has middling beliefs"

msgid "a34365fd24ad4d479c5aacc44656feec"
msgstr "This one has belief in the Hearers’ Vehicle."

msgid "a1fef5a7b4374870964e69e04cf57c2e"
msgstr "This one has wholesome aspirations"

msgid "1a73040f19984a919c969dbdea310ee1"
msgstr ""
"while that one is low, with wrong aspirations.’ “Mañjuśrī, the round sun of "
"the Tathāgata’s awareness does not think"

msgid "3d7c86a9fc164e6c99373ece12706f9a"
msgstr ""
"This sentient being has vast beliefs, so I will teach him the Great Vehicle."

msgid "ad91e20c14a14444aac53d38f8ffa39a"
msgstr "This one has middling beliefs"

msgid "ff64c9a4e520428dbf17d1c79d4468b1"
msgstr "so I will teach him the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle"

msgid "d9f606f1d4e74d869ba8ad2cef084792"
msgstr "This one has belief in the Hearers’ Vehicle,"

msgid "2f5c160d64954840850e2b8639e94420"
msgstr "so I will teach him the Hearers’ Vehicle."

msgid "1ecdc1ca8ae44fd1b537824f133ef806"
msgstr ""
"I shall come to understand the aspirations of sentient beings with either "
"wholesome or unwholesome aspirations"

msgid "56bb5937638f4ce293730f43acc06c89"
msgstr "then purify them"

msgid "da26d907fdfd473ab729c839d3a8bb82"
msgstr ""
"and straighten up their view. Even for sentient beings stuck in what is "
"wrong"

msgid "dceeb1a8b5614b1db882ff5482815995"
msgstr ""
"The light of the rays of awareness from the round sun of the Tathāgata does "
"not have any such concepts."

msgid "c57147cbd6c24a689d9def4df8992c47"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "38e200ebaa524c17a2026e48cd21c25e"
msgstr ""
"On the other hand, Mañjuśrī, because of variations in sentient beings’ "
"inclinations to wholesome intent, the light of the rays of awareness from "
"the round sun of the Tathāgata is varied too."

msgid "21f495ddda3445a6a3db7ffb5bf74303"
msgstr ""
"Because the light of the rays of awareness from the round sun of the "
"Tathāgata has cut off all constructs, concepts, and elaborations."

msgid "a1fe99ef02874e0ebd3950562378a2a6"
msgstr "“It is as follows: Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "0d532a043a9f47f4b88f713e213dc036"
msgstr ""
"in the great ocean there is a great, precious jewel called Fulfilling All "
"Wishes."

msgid "9f275717b3dd4bb4af18389b90c2cec5"
msgstr "I shall teach a fitting dharma."

msgid "945c57ffabf14e139650dfa217f6e408"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, when the teaching of the Dharma is taken as a point of reference "
"for an unreal tathāgata who has not arisen nor ceased, and who is non-"
"existent and primordially unborn,"

msgid "21c41b5d3e1046cb982c923904e8ac5b"
msgstr ""
"the designation ‘the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and Complete Buddha’ "
"becomes established in the world."

msgid "09de21eba1984e2b8b8522b8e3d3a25b"
msgstr ""
"“In the very same way, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and "
"Complete Buddha does not form mental constructs"

msgid "7e00dcf81de14948b067cb37c1cacb0e"
msgstr ""
"It is inconceivable, free from what can be conceived, and free from mind, "
"mentality, and consciousness."

msgid "507916f87a4447c2af6b5f98907e93a5"
msgstr "He does not think or ponder."

msgid "b1055b6f3630484bb75fa108a67eb42a"
msgstr "He is not obtained, not obtainable."

msgid "68e129693d784bc1912057e549c81630"
msgstr ""
"He is inconceivable, free from what can be conceived, and free from mind, "
"mentality, and consciousness."

msgid "da2df99e2703479cad9c6090acbdfa94"
msgstr "He is non-grasping, the act of not holding on."

msgid "f939a82dbfcf43d4965fbb29bdfc6d34"
msgstr ""
"He has eliminated arbitrary truths as well as attachment, aversion, and "
"delusion."

msgid "7f8d33f1887c42c58e755037c8275f25"
msgstr "He is neither true nor false,"

msgid "10d2b4a1571e4ad38b77029a77a5989f"
msgstr "neither permanent nor impermanent,"

msgid "84d3dcb43c274000b29b8d7eadde0f65"
msgstr "neither shining nor not shining,"

msgid "5e1e466f28634dfe813b65182381f295"
msgstr "neither worldly nor non-worldly."

msgid "6e682de348c64d9784f8c11d15844d9f"
msgstr ""
"He is without deliberation or analysis. He is non-arisen and unceasing."

msgid "616cd9e9bce1411ba78f6121f311d1a4"
msgstr ""
"“He is inconceivable, imponderable, essence-less, and not possibly an "
"essence."

msgid "ebe20283316b4bf6bb51cce4ab4ea023"
msgstr "He is empty of non-existence;"

msgid "6f250ecdc63344ebbb209896539dd2ea"
msgstr "He is not bliss,"

msgid "89906e2a9a834db19b40d4ead1de1bcb"
msgstr "he is free from bliss;"

msgid "66d21deef54e43ae8c97a0de0e6f15a4"
msgstr "he is the destruction of bliss."

msgid "509025246b17412abbb71af0a1b21a3d"
msgstr "When it is attached to the top of a banner"

msgid "026f08e86ca24448b0a99b0c811ce1cb"
msgstr ""
"and a sentient being makes a wish, sentient beings will perceive "
"corresponding words coming forth from the jewel. However, that great, "
"precious jewel does not form mental constructs or concepts."

msgid "c9393da9a0a14513aa4441b3cdebba74"
msgstr "He is not a conventional expression;"

msgid "692ca229ce0747e499bc452b8aee98aa"
msgstr "he is the cutting off of conventional expressions."

msgid "a1dccc75835540cda2ab6ec703c698d3"
msgstr "He cannot be clung to."

msgid "c0eac1c5a9f04911aade9a6e21e53263"
msgstr "he is free from striving or giving anything up."

msgid "cdd4107fd1544fad9dace51ff93b62a2"
msgstr "It does not think or ponder."

msgid "7e67e603ccb3448a88bc8c1dc84800d6"
msgstr "He cannot be counted;"

msgid "53f00ab491624c7cbe295251d6fbddbb"
msgstr "he is free from counting."

msgid "653bb5575a7f447da9b99cfb89890cf1"
msgstr "and has cut off all conventional expressions."

msgid "3e66c652e6a647768c502cf7dfd5cc54"
msgstr "he has cut off all movement"

msgid "27cf7be1e9524f5aa1735e4bcc9c2f07"
msgstr "He is not movement, he has reached non-movement;"

msgid "47efd2adc14245b68e167c70c4800b95"
msgstr "He is not space,"

msgid "09820680cd85449e8b8410684d45a8b1"
msgstr "he is ungraspable."

msgid "81a06ed18ff44a05a7f9f663007d37f1"
msgstr "“He cannot be seen or beholden,"

msgid "65cf0bc719e242809d3c3f1985656739"
msgstr "not lack of space."

msgid "bc7f990e96324405a1bd898cd65f6319"
msgstr "not an assemblage,"

msgid "d1d0094acc9c4482b9a4d7f328ed5b19"
msgstr "and not a non-assemblage."

msgid "eb6732a795974f31897439db0861a826"
msgstr "He is neither mentally constructed nor not mentally constructed."

msgid "2823750686e244ffa58d070eeb184d6c"
msgstr "He is not visible,"

msgid "6472d9a1aad1480d88f2f23dc9efeb9e"
msgstr "not to be described,"

msgid "d0143223a8464c06923486bfc5541cbf"
msgstr "He is not established, shown, afflicted, or purified."

msgid "2b2308f2c4aa4a8e8c7ce2cb839cafa4"
msgstr "He is not established, shown, afflicted, or purified."

msgid "d2bcc1ad73e54aec975d36a260a71c48"
msgstr "He is not name,"

msgid "8a5bccfab028470b96bcab3c62f95952"
msgstr "not form,"

msgid "1c0549ee581a405782fd0a4e23040e54"
msgstr "not sign;"

msgid "c6c302deb4fb41fb8a6a4d1db70b90c4"
msgstr "not karma,"

msgid "a93a861a18044e90bfb5a21cb34839c7"
msgstr "not the maturation of karma."

msgid "103c319b54944ceb8585e7430f7c36c3"
msgstr "He is not past,"

msgid "1608fb2537c54e06816c8dc32ed7d32a"
msgstr "not future,"

msgid "e60fa6c2e0144ab8b39651470c620117"
msgstr "not present."

msgid "e2b1f5dbd05b43c4a63393a344c3ed86"
msgstr "He is nothing whatsoever."

msgid "b4aab87e47904c33bd22a9fa7e0a9030"
msgstr "He is without impurity,"

msgid "28e7a971de6d4b019858554ebfd2a093"
msgstr "without syllables,"

msgid "71156059f55d4b25b49fe74355ab25e2"
msgstr "without voice,"

msgid "dc31721f435e469c97ed3c8b7029f3d5"
msgstr "not speech."

msgid "0212521c5a2446358897bfab6aab5ab5"
msgstr "beyond a voice,"

msgid "19eb7de07a9c4dc7a361bd8c8fcda47a"
msgstr "He is not a characteristic,"

msgid "acd321d967eb4bf5b1ef714a7f87431f"
msgstr "he is free from all characteristics;"

msgid "54cf2529a3674ef5823f3817fe87a999"
msgstr "not perceived inside, outside, or in between."

msgid "2b2b6def9fd945cf8f72cd227379192d"
msgstr ""
"“And Mañjuśrī, the awareness jewel of the Tathāgata is completely pure in "
"its intent, and is fixed at the top of the banner of great compassion."

msgid "15f7a4bc3e2446b6a65e13c8a22fa983"
msgstr ""
"According to his or her inclinations and beliefs, a sentient being perceives"
" a Dharma teaching issuing forth from that jewel."

msgid "a4b7bfe7a131408fbe6380dc7c705549"
msgstr ""
"And in this respect, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata is the same, neutral, without "
"concepts, and does not make any distinctions."

msgid "fdf4f03e0f8d47bdb82c7fc0045162e7"
msgstr "“It is as follows: Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "acdd96f9e4f74b528c23e2772b3385a8"
msgstr ""
"sentient beings perceive an echo issuing forth as the intimation of someone "
"else’s speech."

msgid "1ab7f56d83a34c718358ea0b774d008a"
msgstr "“But that echo is not past, future, or present."

msgid "2b9cd85c365b4b7ead4a51732e45c5f6"
msgstr "It cannot be perceived inside, outside, or in between."

msgid "55b2f9d48956474d9656d9db51a2480a"
msgstr "It is non-arisen"

msgid "3b3da1fbb6c64a02baad76ddfa04d6f4"
msgstr "and unceasing."

msgid "862126576003426e843c38524ad107bd"
msgstr "It is not cut off,"

msgid "73bf9cddf84c4797bd072dcfc8563c40"
msgstr "not permanent;"

msgid "de7fcd612b5b46fea58852cba6321307"
msgstr "it is not endowed with awareness,"

msgid "93edded14c684839a481c6e54aae9fb4"
msgstr "nor is it without awareness."

msgid "fb194127945749a4950381ca8f169eb9"
msgstr "It is neither wisdom"

msgid "17814826acf44cf98cc802022efe70e4"
msgstr "nor not wisdom,"

msgid "f49ed0e544b04852baf78f8636d08848"
msgstr "neither knowledge"

msgid "b6a8c788a8624e27a6788adf743fdf36"
msgstr "nor ignorance,"

msgid "74ecaafe83ec4c1794fb021d85e9bf9b"
msgstr "neither liberation"

msgid "43d94fdcf6d6475ca739152ee253cdd3"
msgstr "nor not liberation."

msgid "40b20326ad0c46618e1f30d5dc2a5c1c"
msgstr "“It is neither blameworthy"

msgid "5ddc41be357e45e6ba6a75f535feba1c"
msgstr "nor free from blame,"

msgid "87970af0082d4ab8ad2469f28d7f3e0d"
msgstr "neither recollection"

msgid "ff97fb3ee30046d6971f71fd3e382ede"
msgstr "nor non-recollection,"

msgid "83cc0f866ed64b8e9e7f15df694ebf35"
msgstr "neither placed"

msgid "808ea677cde94de684bb200559914ed0"
msgstr "nor unplaced,"

msgid "90167222b4d6442a9dc95f9a429bc505"
msgstr "nor not sitting."

msgid "83be6d6d7d3448f5a3f8cdf48423d66c"
msgstr "neither sitting"

msgid "24198ee7df1c429c8dd6a04d3e19ee2f"
msgstr "It is not the earth element,"

msgid "262a782513cb4ac8b82cddae6118e2b8"
msgstr "not the water element,"

msgid "3201ae0c1ebb47778277eec71e56ab4f"
msgstr "not the fire element,"

msgid "edcb195f670e4cf38d89421826335a3f"
msgstr "and not the wind element."

msgid "63a5dce4ec0c4f558195e6c21048f958"
msgstr "It is neither co-produced"

msgid "c32fe1b5df404a1ca10ad7ae0fdedfaa"
msgstr "nor unproduced,"

msgid "66f3c4013a5d4391996e920c3f9f4673"
msgstr "neither free from elaboration"

msgid "717d4e6879604667851a2d52d4724242"
msgstr "nor with elaboration,"

msgid "f946bc5490bc4ddf9cf54267c2d36aea"
msgstr "neither speech"

msgid "aa63ff1d12b342709f5d963393eee1d1"
msgstr "nor not speech,"

msgid "dbdc8e4fbc0a48168d5155b877a548b0"
msgstr "and neither visible"

msgid "ed4ac571b90d4db784e0062b141e3acf"
msgstr "nor invisible."

msgid "49ecd072aa124119b41b22fe2776d17a"
