msgid "bfc039a4fecd48dcaf7a5513e4797fa5"
msgstr "without voice,"

msgid "adc2d07ef26a43c8a0ca4afb0463c810"
msgstr "beyond voice"

msgid "b091e21138694bbaa182774f5b5c938d"
msgstr "without comparison,"

msgid "8e6d279d986a4463993d8eaed5ea225c"
msgstr "beyond comparison,"

msgid "ec01ee9243f44cf5b238c27561e4b2c8"
msgstr "not a characteristic,"

msgid "bf197c0bdee745d98a47715747ed3346"
msgstr "free from characteristics."

msgid "821d913d67194933945b99dace1756ea"
msgstr "It is neither peace nor not peace,"

msgid "1173a2c2ec184acb83a3ab34ba28af44"
msgstr "neither long nor short,"

msgid "86bb23b32b664d969cf5a2055f7d2b24"
msgstr "neither sentient nor insentient,"

msgid "1a575f76a5ff4fbc9b360818237d85cb"
msgstr "neither mental nor not mental."

msgid "82d4778255f64ccdae90b4fa94ec0b63"
msgstr "It is neither to be beheld, nor not to be beheld."

msgid "b0448a8f61b54c1891b6e436cca915fa"
msgstr "free from mind, mentality, and consciousness."

msgid "acbe0855825a4e1f89391b36707519d6"
msgstr "not analysis,"

msgid "a13de814a48d459daf6f036bbd226fff"
msgstr "It is not deliberation,"

msgid "d6c45487176c4218b74cf53501061cd9"
msgstr "It is empty of the nature of seeing."

msgid "5450b8bbc54b4740b9d6dfd5f4c318c9"
msgstr "It is non-recollection,"

msgid "3dc0a8f376584c7694f72ffb6c6a8bd9"
msgstr "non-mental-placement."

msgid "e9230d2e0efd4768beb45e4c8490541f"
msgstr ""
"In all regards it is the same, neutral, without concepts, and does not make "
"any distinctions."

msgid "f28b7899f0334c59a299d68ef9a4fa03"
msgstr "It is beyond the three times."

msgid "5ca0284fd735414ea408e4015c60c004"
msgstr "However,"

msgid "ba8d0b24a4a1460693c5afce363203a5"
msgstr ""
"“In the very same way, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and "
"Complete Buddha is not past, future, or present."

msgid "96f25abaeee94498b4a13e36c1a2108c"
msgstr "He cannot be perceived inside, outside, or in between."

msgid "22bca5678f164ccb81c7ae41fb035d93"
msgstr "He is non-arisen"

msgid "9bb39ba7437e46d5a1bf6abdd8a004c9"
msgstr "unceasing."

msgid "444466acc97e43ff97a984959e7f3761"
msgstr "He is not cut off,"

msgid "0a4f208e555840d6a167615bd67a5d2e"
msgstr "not permanent;"

msgid "486d9061176e4c85bac9dba034d816fb"
msgstr "he is not endowed with awareness, nor is he without awareness."

msgid "35759fab1fa44ba88f41d2fe7552aac3"
msgstr "He is neither with wisdom nor without wisdom."

msgid "7fe4546c9de74f3ea1132e1416066b7b"
msgstr "He is neither knowledge nor ignorance,"

msgid "9a3c768ce070492f85babe41918c486a"
msgstr "neither liberation nor not liberation."

msgid "20ff0856145f46c7a0b4ce4110cad085"
msgstr "“He is neither blameworthy nor free from blame,"

msgid "65d6c8c4e89d4f90a958c5af076b8aa6"
msgstr "neither with recollection nor without recollection,"

msgid "ccd93402fa89410cb6cfcd8e9f1e9cb1"
msgstr "neither placed nor unplaced,"

msgid "dca7e27d4c0e465c98b399dc8f35ad32"
msgstr "neither sitting nor not sitting."

msgid "8cddd955b66c4fdea6237fd29e04450a"
msgstr "He is not the earth element,"

msgid "0ff29068b4634999bbefcfe4eb7bbc9c"
msgstr "not the water element,"

msgid "904b731d1fc54a56b295eb46496b9b44"
msgstr "not the fire element,"

msgid "fb98ebdbd96c4cb9b916d3bf87faec7a"
msgstr "and not the wind element."

msgid "0a4096db96804095a2ac09064526706d"
msgstr "and sentient beings perceive it to be just that way."

msgid "bb7b1bb0d93441e6ad9d930975fda8d1"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, the echo, the voice of many sounds, comes forth for sentient "
"beings with varied inclinations, as the intimation of the voice of many "
"sounds,"

msgid "43c21b49377a48e698614c1ec4356000"
msgstr "not the water element,"

msgid "5049618026f245d79925db5e93c6c675"
msgstr "not the fire element,"

msgid "61b8a2f1f8ff4926a3e72f466f15c31c"
msgstr "and not the wind element."

msgid "38f6863d04924b4e8e46634a3d19c8a8"
msgstr "He is neither co-produced nor unproduced,"

msgid "77816b28bb0f482181a22a6e11e6099c"
msgstr "neither elaboration nor non-elaboration,"

msgid "801467a52ad54c9aaa6264c9eadcf32b"
msgstr "neither speech nor not speech,"

msgid "7395c8847c4f40e48acd055235c43fe9"
msgstr "and neither visible nor invisible."

msgid "469262fed754411db050956386d544b3"
msgstr "“He is without syllables,"

msgid "53f5255f09734cbb82b24c3f1685c3a2"
msgstr "without voice,"

msgid "a21af9a37f2648f48f6fb48119f7bf79"
msgstr "beyond voice,"

msgid "7cf9d5806d6e40cc9fdeb39dc50cc5b8"
msgstr "without comparison,"

msgid "c2c3666935c44583b8bcaa574d5d8ae8"
msgstr "beyond comparison,"

msgid "86e82f7937fc4615b1b34499bb3b7715"
msgstr "not a characteristic,"

msgid "8b8d497d9ac640d59d8f2d806a29df71"
msgstr "free from characteristics."

msgid "f41ef8ea54e546e88dc862b2a4cf3fde"
msgstr "He is neither peaceful nor not peaceful,"

msgid "cb92ee780d8042948c60fd766fb24b31"
msgstr "neither long nor short,"

msgid "896b6424ac344b2585f9c5bb8c9507dd"
msgstr "neither mental nor not mental."

msgid "af4ac9a5343d46989667337b4ea25d5c"
msgstr "He is neither to be beheld, nor not to be beheld."

msgid "f8f0d2f5ad6c4989a16efd9658001269"
msgstr "He is non-recollection"

msgid "92d565e8840042cda62ca5514b7cbff1"
msgstr "He is empty of the nature of seeing."

msgid "cd201216fd904f35bb98e1cc809831b0"
msgstr "and non-mental-placement."

msgid "d6167cd9f7ff4de09b039cc6c17eb743"
msgstr "He is not deliberation,"

msgid "ba28b8e302af410da99f894d46805c21"
msgstr "not analysis,"

msgid "ae3472880c97408a8278c685c9dc33a9"
msgstr "and free from mind, mentality, and consciousness."

msgid "75175be220e84839b74e26df79a5e2d3"
msgstr "He is beyond the three times."

msgid "7151959673014ae1b0fc41d9dfd11902"
msgstr ""
"In all regards he is the same, neutral, without concepts, and does not make "
"any distinctions."

msgid "2c81f3ff396244e0ac5e5f1232cbe5c0"
msgstr "Yet, Mañjuśrī, sentient beings with varied beliefs perceive"

msgid "5deafe09c5ed456f8da00bbeda593b96"
msgstr ""
"Yet, Mañjuśrī, sentient beings with varied beliefs perceive the speech of "
"the Tathāgata, issuing forth in accordance with their manifold inclinations."

msgid "895ec35baf7945a1938ce675ece57b28"
msgstr ""
"the speech of the Tathāgata, issuing forth in accordance with their manifold"
" inclinations."

msgid "6e68f19f9a934344a1651a778c6f8b0c"
msgstr "“It is as follows: Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "861f7a2a40894000abefbec3aa47fb95"
msgstr ""
"it is through having the earth as their basis and support that all grass, "
"thickets, herbs, and trees grow to become sizeable."

msgid "4174227fe3af482fa18363b59eb1ecc1"
msgstr "But, Mañjuśrī, the earth does not form mental constructs or concepts."

msgid "4224d037f9f04047a31e3eba61b2e34d"
msgstr "With respect to everything it is the same, free from concepts,"

msgid "e6abaa30866449efad99e6697f6e72c7"
msgstr "and free from mind, mentality, and consciousness."

msgid "e6c6c75bc7084fe5b4deb7c1b3ea891b"
msgstr "and free from mind, mentality, and consciousness."

msgid "5d9611edb5c64c458f8d4f75fbd3680a"
msgstr "free from distinctions."

msgid "de024f2dc9274af0a332e7c8232f837f"
msgstr "It is free from speculations"

msgid "3ebcfddc51974072b28f2e61c2345f7d"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, Mañjuśrī, it is through having the Tathāgata as their "
"basis and support"

msgid "24d76ca131f040e0b64b5cdaf58b30d9"
msgstr ""
"or of all tīrthikas such as the Carakas, Parivrājakas, and Nirgranthas, and "
"so forth; or of any others, down to the roots of what is wholesome of those "
"stuck in what is wrong; it is through having the Tathāgata as their basis "
"and support that they grow and become sizeable."

msgid "3cff6bb7d1904afc92894d831363d84c"
msgstr ""
"that all the roots of what is wholesome of all sentient beings grow and "
"become sizeable. Whether it is the roots of what is wholesome of those on "
"the Vehicle of the Hearers, on the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle, or on the Great "
"Vehicle;"

msgid "483137845a0f472f9ee70dad8f4a1232"
msgstr ""
"“However, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata does not form mental constructs or "
"concepts."

msgid "4da1d3849ed64299a3a6b4096fa7cf90"
msgstr ""
"or of all tīrthikas such as the Carakas, Parivrājakas, and Nirgranthas, and "
"so forth; or of any others, down to the roots of what is wholesome of those "
"stuck in what is wrong; it is through having the Tathāgata as their basis "
"and support that they grow and become sizeable."

msgid "dbe03139a4b245d9a96992fc59f31b05"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and Complete Buddha has cut "
"off all mental constructs, concepts, points of reference, and mental "
"engagement."

msgid "01fc0cf1b1ba4105890695f18c58775a"
msgstr "He is free from mind, mentality, and consciousness;"

msgid "c6ff64edb3a54c7fa8d0216868882a43"
msgstr "he is neither speculation nor the domain of speculation."

msgid "d94ec625c8554bb9b012bb751f68cd42"
msgstr "He is invisible,"

msgid "0a42861244a94d21a44461f0ac2359bb"
msgstr "not to be beheld,"

msgid "cea59c364c1d4ec09faec3520b68aa46"
msgstr "not an object of thought or deliberation."

msgid "a0d63dc09b264aa6b0e51ec7582ffd87"
msgstr "free from thought,"

msgid "f57282a431654d42ac378feb40f542c9"
msgstr "It is free from mind, mentality, and consciousness."

msgid "ea2dde7808474da9b55acf4bbf5f6338"
msgstr ""
"With respect to all, he is the same, neutral, without concepts, and he does "
"not make any distinctions."

msgid "bfcd0dbb7c084919a6df5a89e901908e"
msgstr "“It is as follows: Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "24b618880089415cadfb9de1b42a7584"
msgstr "space is everywhere the same,"

msgid "c0f017f7cece46348d96ab64f1eb01e1"
msgstr "free from concepts"

msgid "87be7e10157c4c0a927e460951a2809b"
msgstr "and distinctions."

msgid "a5a74fcb83af457481cb4f74c9110420"
msgstr "It is non-arisen"

msgid "ac28a86b2ef74ab1aa55db2a26ca7d64"
msgstr "and unceasing;"

msgid "3a2024db80844b559561658ffc141c39"
msgstr "it is not past, future, or present."

msgid "9033754fea824300947afc0a7a757fbb"
msgstr "It is indefinable,"

msgid "38947d7ac21d46f4a949e85e26dc951e"
msgstr "non-elaborate,"

msgid "f0df6ccf8f6441d9a5e3899e4a4efe33"
msgstr "and formless;"

msgid "57ae9e912a2048c58ae200558a24c8fa"
msgstr "it cannot be shown"

msgid "8c7a4a0829f948dc836374f2180a1541"
msgstr "or made known."

msgid "8337e551edc0425ab7a887268bfe2cd9"
msgstr "It is without contact,"

msgid "a54f4c0b7e694a95b90752220c7e1c05"
msgstr "without dwelling,"

msgid "a82a273956174773a9850bd4fd89709c"
msgstr "not comparable,"

msgid "2b24cd0401db4835b5a3623c9bd73de7"
msgstr "and beyond compare."

msgid "4e2bfae0e09449d9be0be07fb522b0f3"
msgstr "It has no simile"

msgid "90ca19e5c89442ca965c77dc399a73f4"
msgstr "and is beyond all similes."

msgid "03bcad1c6a024841a9b119ea25037571"
msgstr "It has no basis;"

msgid "f51a017d72724553bdd42236ec6834ab"
msgstr "it is ungraspable"

msgid "e9178c9a0aa74bf0873eca5634882337"
msgstr "and beyond visible range."

msgid "6e9c53b1e8c349469af4e15dcfee103f"
msgstr "It has no characteristic;"

msgid "2080f32b23094dbf8c96197dc61207d0"
msgstr "it is without syllables, voice, and mental engagement."

msgid "81cea1261db14206aa9e4238a58fbcdd"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, sentient beings experience space as being low or high, according "
"to whether the place is low, middling, or high."

msgid "7fcb54a1954e46c88458df4ab27f8dfd"
msgstr "It is beyond the realm of words."

msgid "d5f50ea19a4f46e0abedfbebb7ba97d9"
msgstr "It reaches and enters everywhere. And still,"

msgid "2f6ba88e7a31412a9e1d28d9d33b2600"
msgstr "It has no striving or giving up;"

msgid "857dceefa7924f6ab0b34b6f24b703e1"
msgstr "no removal,"

msgid "f0ff0f00699340fe9a1dce76bc896571"
msgstr "no addition."

msgid "527baec9448e4bb98e91cedf9d95e64c"
msgstr "He is without mental engagement,"

msgid "dedea42aac914c05888a7a44f2e9701b"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and "
"Complete Buddha is everywhere the same, free from concepts and distinctions."

msgid "5194e0bc9d7e47888a96523a1880c452"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, sentient beings experience space as being low or high, according "
"to whether the place is low, middling, or high."

msgid "80e4eebdbaa54c9caa6a2b388f7d4acd"
msgstr "He is non-arisen"

msgid "69b648651b994e028f8bb569e19d1318"
msgstr "and unceasing,"

msgid "501ef537fca5438b96141c15a525bd70"
msgstr "he is not past, future, or present."

msgid "1ad88b6f7f0e406d8f7feb676f3dc43e"
msgstr "He is indefinable,"

msgid "26bdcc6456d44c1ca945d7df6055f318"
msgstr "non-elaborate,"

msgid "b4c630cbd71445349277d00b3850127d"
msgstr "and formless;"

msgid "baabf087157e4fbf891cfad4472a88bd"
msgstr "he cannot be shown or made known."

msgid "5b991bdaaa20473b897463a8966d6102"
msgstr "He is without contact,"

msgid "fad4b4126f6c4a449cf4d1fd7dab2149"
msgstr "without dwelling,"

msgid "9f2ca1e8183a407089a01c913b60d878"
msgstr "not comparable,"

msgid "2a80d880a839449ca4c9ca1890559323"
msgstr "and beyond compare."

msgid "bc6f8f0470ba4e15bfec0068085f23c7"
msgstr "He has no simile"

msgid "3642a40a7f6b493db62b5f3c31d61286"
msgstr "and is beyond all similes."

msgid "0633f2dcea444d23bef941968cd04230"
msgstr "He has no basis,"

msgid "e514ef2a3a0846499793a359e054c53c"
msgstr "he is ungraspable"

msgid "1fcb2d663da94295aa41e2431bb7401d"
msgstr "and beyond visible range."

msgid "39ff31fd658a4f79a3d86c52cb79c664"
msgstr "He is free from mind, mentality, and consciousness."

msgid "a79d389c238e46c2bd486b1348b01daa"
msgstr "He has no characteristic;"

msgid "6463a133a83346d08c9408ff05c7aa85"
msgstr "he is without syllables, voice, and mental engagement."

msgid "a6c0c362676349bba083b1a136c703df"
msgstr "He reaches and enters everywhere."

msgid "7d89c535d5664bd2b6aa772edcf05a2f"
msgstr "He is beyond the realm of words."

msgid "434cb2e5909c46868ce86a60ab295624"
msgstr ""
"And still, Mañjuśrī, according to whether sentient beings are low, middling,"
" or high,"

msgid "09ceca76ce9c40dd85bf7f1240af5e46"
msgstr "they see the Tathāgata as low, middling, or high."

msgid "7812e3eff84b4571af75f11717da1355"
msgstr "“Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata does not think,"

msgid "ddbb41a0710f4cdbbbe12d077d8e104c"
msgstr ""
"‘This sentient being has low inclinations and beliefs, so I will show him a "
"low perfection of the form body."

msgid "22244815d506403f84629a0331e370b9"
msgstr ""
"This sentient being has middling inclinations and beliefs, so I will show "
"him a middling perfection of the form body."

msgid "4ecd467cf21042d79e36b88ae294b503"
msgstr "This sentient being has vast inclinations and beliefs,"

msgid "58b9b07054344c42adf138e5423a4a1a"
msgstr "so I will show him a vast perfection of the form body.’"

msgid "86e5a33cbeb54f3a8aa9e84ceaafbead"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, this is also what you should understand regarding how the Dharma "
"is taught."

msgid "42f26ccc6c6045b9bdbe3d0b0497250b"
msgstr "so for him I shall make a speech relating to the Hearers’ Vehicle."

msgid "bb97e27100134b429466cea7603a6943"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata does not think, ‘This sentient being has low "
"beliefs,"

msgid "92dc0ea3d3e54fc3925c4f1075888919"
msgstr "This sentient being has middling beliefs,"

msgid "c0919e6a2f95446a9743526928af9634"
msgstr ""
"so for him I shall make a speech relating to the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle."

msgid "65cb0bfd6db34454a5005e862e8660cb"
msgstr "no removal,"

msgid "95447c123d744d45a658c4ff2621b897"
msgstr "no addition."

msgid "5c01f49da1994f9d9eec553816e3b38b"
msgstr "He has no striving or giving up;"

msgid "e30fb3bba9fb431d9c0b051560e73a88"
msgstr ""
"so for him I shall make a speech relating to the Pratyekabuddha Vehicle."

msgid "f11fab9842ed41e6acde0aeec292b898"
msgstr "This sentient being has vast beliefs,"

msgid "1d50705ae3a74aac8909ef6498a95c8c"
msgstr "so for him I shall make a speech relating to the Great Vehicle.’"

msgid "5d27bdbfeddf431a91283b8debf3d6f6"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata does not think, ‘This sentient being has belief in "
"giving,"

msgid "854f0b76588048e1a794a358a2fd2bcb"
msgstr "so for him I shall make a speech related to giving.’"

msgid "0cae03126e84416c8ebd6b7fa35b837b"
msgstr ""
"Nor does he think so for discipline, forbearance, diligence, or "
"concentration."

msgid "291a6759c5b8429ca23376f804111c93"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata is the dharmakāya."

msgid "e8124aa382464b38934310a2b2d92424"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata is utterly non-arisen."

msgid "6f3f3b72b43c42608bc6746f8ae6675b"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, for the Tathāgata, a consciousness chasing after names, forms, "
"and etymological explanations does not occur."

msgid "4a6c412e99f04581a079fa641735183c"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata does not form mental constructs or concepts."

msgid "4954974b2b7f4178a768089b1874b88c"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata is momentary,"

msgid "4a0d14bf015c45068a5159d315cc588d"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata does not think, ‘This sentient being has belief in "
"the perfection of wisdom, so for him I shall make a speech related to the "
"perfection of wisdom.’"

msgid "3e5f4dc674d54710811b3b41867af09e"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata does not think in that way."

msgid "5de3c0109a6848f8b5c4708ad7a35cde"
msgstr "and his characteristic is to be inexhaustible."

msgid "16fcf05903e24f36aa2aa951142d83dc"
msgstr ""
"He is fixed at the pinnacle of non-exhaustion, the pinnacle of reality."

msgid "8cb55360b6014857a0aafcec61b327f7"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and Complete Buddha"

msgid "3c44bf54ac954756b4f2b552ea8d973c"
msgstr ""
"is the pinnacle of the sameness of all dharmas, the pinnacle of their non-"
"duality, and the pinnacle of their utter non-arising."

msgid "88d36af8d31142f384f3f33b3f032138"
msgstr "He is not low, nor middling, nor high."

msgid "fcd5e9a4962f4d8c937cdd56e6053bef"
msgstr ""
"In all regards he is the same, free from concepts, and free from "
"distinctions."

msgid "c9189820d4e04cd19df4b33c24a49ff8"
msgstr "They are not low, nor middling, nor high."

msgid "90ad9c2d422c48819f8c8eea57308a58"
msgstr "It is because no dharmas are perceived."

msgid "0fe962c52f894e448d84ad93bd8f9c85"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, just in the same way, all dharmas are same free from concepts, "
"and free from distinctions."

msgid "2d106d99059448ddb96851750d46a382"
msgstr "And why is that?"

msgid "9ef3914e763f4f259fe38734bfcb41c8"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, this non-perception of all dharmas is their sameness."

msgid "bfcfada2a20040cd873619adb020b42c"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, this non-perception of all dharmas is their sameness."

msgid "e34514fa2a2d4b8795c9932959b738d6"
msgstr "Their sameness is their remaining fixed."

msgid "2fc4c80bbe99442a91800f6bfe40d456"
msgstr "Remaining fixed means that they do not move;"

msgid "ab4074ab33fa4f18bbc3aed915c77674"
msgstr "not moving means being without any abode."

msgid "e053a630aa7b4de395cdd325d789ca8c"
msgstr ""
"“For someone with no abode in any dharma, the mind has no place to stand."

msgid "c342bb86c59549b098f7ee8ca30dd0c2"
msgstr "For a mind that stands nowhere, there will be non-arising."

msgid "d03107f28c8544bdab7ef4e118e26a58"
msgstr ""
"And for someone who sees in this way, no distorted mind and mental states "
"come about;"

msgid "da0e55123a9b40f6a4b39ac818fdce48"
msgstr "someone whose mind is undistorted will have authentic attainment."

msgid "dcbcb97a37424c9e924ba9e317ee6e56"
msgstr "“Whoever has authentic attainment will not form elaborations."

msgid "d69d76d85a1548d0bee37b6465b1dcfc"
msgstr "Someone who does not form elaborations does not move about."

msgid "6c6c77976b1b4434a3bc39fd59b237f2"
msgstr "When one does not move about, one does not wander."

msgid "97164ed27a2e4226a1698b576d4101c4"
msgstr "When one does not wander, one does not become distracted."

msgid "9cbd4a4252304a1eb6d84e9e8fbe76f6"
msgstr "One who does not become distracted does not oppose the dharmatā."

msgid "2f60e184fa0046958318f20502497782"
msgstr ""
"One who does not oppose the dharmatā is in conformity with everything."

msgid "edeabc0293f94452b5c3914581dd2dc8"
msgstr ""
"One who is in conformity with everything does not move from the nature of "
"the dharmas."

msgid "457b89552a5740ef8aa6b1b3a09ef276"
msgstr ""
"One who does not move from the nature of the dharmas obtains the nature of "
"the dharmas."

msgid "7dab6dfefc014f4f975b21566c1b0fbe"
msgstr ""
"One who obtains the nature of the dharmas does not form any elaboration."

msgid "0e056d1629ee4913a0e29497de4cc09b"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "102abf8f2af34bf783d841f831f84841"
msgstr "“Whoever is born from conditions and causes is utterly unborn."

msgid "505500b089384d88a013975784e55380"
msgstr "Someone utterly unborn has gained certainty."

msgid "92987e0cf6dd49e28877cf3167b2e611"
msgstr ""
"Whoever has gained certainty does not dwell with any mental engagement in "
"the dharmas."

msgid "f5e522834cc84d85917605d2590c86ed"
msgstr ""
"When one does not dwell with any mental engagement in the dharmas, one does "
"not dwell with the dharmas."

msgid "a87b304a908f44379f9f51f0680ff7ce"
msgstr ""
"When one does not dwell with the dharmas, one does not come into existence "
"or go out of existence."

msgid "4a07fffae8ab4a308b0fa5f5c6b4c7f2"
msgstr ""
"When one does not come into existence or go out of existence, one becomes "
"fixed and has obtained the Dharma."

msgid "b7fde55ecc5c408dbc823676ee7ae4b1"
msgstr ""
"“When one becomes fixed and has obtained the Dharma, one applies oneself to "
"the proper dharma."

msgid "50b52943f868428ead67d61fd40a46e9"
msgstr ""
"When one applies oneself to the proper dharma, no dharma whatsoever is not a"
" buddhadharma."

msgid "488838cacbe8468f8dde42ce3825308c"
msgstr "Due to the realization of emptiness."

msgid "71ac5c78f856402db5a1df928f002917"
msgstr "The realization of emptiness is awakening."

msgid "dd876a6a5f234dbab0145b1185dee845"
msgstr "no-sign,"

msgid "c41013b78ba640b1b1221a4f4818ff00"
msgstr "no-wish;"

msgid "f098a342908f4fd994ca1c79cc44ce71"
msgstr "no-dwelling,"

msgid "24916341a4f44220a4cda4f8c5cbea17"
msgstr "no-effort,"

msgid "1c26146f790148b99e98f010a88d1ce8"
msgstr ""
"“It is awakening, because in this way one realizes emptiness, no-sign, no-"
"wish; no-effort, no-dwelling, no coming about; no object of apprehension and"
" no-abode."

msgid "df58d561c3bc40a68736b2c58fd04d49"
msgstr "Awakening is proper application."

msgid "8242117fbfec4122bb6fadc4605baebf"
msgstr "“What is called proper application is to neither remove nor add."

msgid "9da9e48652de4f0fad593625b22c99e5"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "6b96d2a9c8e941d4a7799084d09761b4"
msgstr "and the application of what has yet to come."

msgid "20c0b1cf6ab44058b95221cbec056fea"
msgstr "This is proper application."

msgid "49a24396faab49fc878ab2bf532c6cc3"
msgstr "It is the non-liberated application,"

msgid "6eec2a5e2d01431f863f44cd1c8ac4da"
msgstr "and it is not connected."

msgid "357331d0c58b4466afc347db4ca086c8"
msgstr "It is the application of not doing and not changing,"

msgid "9e42bc1e523e491990874dcf64672bff"
msgstr "the application of neither oneness nor plurality,"

msgid "695192f79d804b1bacf01f32b9d29cfe"
msgstr "Because mind is by nature luminous."

msgid "90885bc953ae404c977ce89589d12dd8"
msgstr "“In that respect, there is no application,"

msgid "8fe26a6535db47caa2a2b92ca2ab5fbc"
msgstr "no measure"

msgid "c14f03b8a7504f9a815c7cd9c0d15084"
msgstr "and no direct realization of a result."

msgid "16e2b8fbcbfb4537ae736ce834ee484f"
msgstr "It is afflicted by adventitious afflictions,"

msgid "cdd3cc91d98f4a3a84cb7e132ebebd26"
msgstr "but its nature is not afflicted."

msgid "ab8b75572a7a46b09fdf9c08744ca900"
msgstr "“Luminosity by nature is non-affliction."

msgid "c087b48ee9694d5b8891dde30fa8e94e"
msgstr ""
"With respect to non-affliction there is no counteragent—a counteragent by "
"which the destruction of the afflictions may occur."

msgid "9d20afe7f90946b1a4503c11f818bf79"
msgstr "Because what is pure does not become pure; it just is pure."

msgid "cdf8fa3356874d268e3a6756fda8557a"
msgstr "“That which is pure is non-arising."

msgid "32f501868c3141f4841045afab8bff0d"
msgstr "Non-arising is faultless."

msgid "f6507d01173f4ddeb342c3f8a774206b"
msgstr "What is faultless is the destruction of joys,"

msgid "822cb0420a3e420e8db1676096886146"
msgstr "whereby all attachments cease."

msgid "06378e83395346c89c477fa2ec0b262c"
msgstr "Where all attachments cease, that is non-arising."

msgid "ac586e4c992a40b6a031b4b63f79473a"
msgstr "And non-arising is awakening."

msgid "4c72832f9aa7414c814087aa199fe211"
msgstr "“Awakening is sameness."

msgid "91e275af78844258826ccc86ea9212d4"
msgstr "Sameness is the tathatā."

msgid "af2bcfa1a58542c99d7e499e4708eb16"
msgstr "All dharmas, co-produced and unproduced, abide in the tathatā."

msgid "734b1bcffe124536b33f849e1413589d"
msgstr "there is no designation of duality."

msgid "f0284423940f4407bfbc297b6e795569"
msgstr "With respect to the tathatā there is neither something co-produced"

msgid "50c06811b9ef4ad18d5eca794f8d9af4"
msgstr ""
"Where there is nothing co-produced or unproduced, and no designation of "
"duality, that is the tathatā."

msgid "054c4e6286cc4c659eaa9fdff601cbd2"
msgstr "nor something unproduced;"

msgid "48291da576954675a3fe43a812169eb8"
msgstr "“The tathatā is nothing else but the tathatā."

msgid "559e5973fe2d40c5a8c662559d484166"
msgstr "Nothing else but the tathatā is the unchanging tathatā."

msgid "a0603269defc43f3a6ff0b3eaa3dc0a2"
msgstr "The unchanging tathatā is the non-coming tathatā."

msgid "4ed3302111fb4b4fb28db03bb3ed3f13"
msgstr "The unchanging tathatā is the non-coming tathatā."

msgid "8d294b398cdb4094972cddedaeaf3260"
msgstr "The non-coming tathatā is the tathatā that does not go."

msgid "59616fd39b2f41b6b915ed4b74104bd6"
msgstr "The tathatā that does not go is the authentic tathatā."

msgid "c892e44914d4440a8199ff6a8d176e3c"
msgstr "The authentic tathatā is the not-at-all-tathatā."

msgid "cd80d09d40b747a2a3e524fe2d01d2cc"
msgstr "The not-at-all-tathatā is not afflicted"

msgid "3869ff56cf3d431e80db71b11861eb1e"
msgstr "and is not purified."

msgid "f205ab436a0644c8a889a6d41478eb40"
msgstr ""
"That which is neither afflicted nor purified neither arises nor ceases."

msgid "517a59bad98043c6ba9e1d4c62f1c45c"
msgstr "That which neither arises nor ceases is the same as nirvāṇa."

msgid "9061a501dc8640d9a39cfc3091d0285c"
msgstr ""
"That which is the same as nirvāṇa neither roams within saṃsāra nor passes "
"into complete nirvāṇa."

msgid "906aa1baaf9943159aaf6aa4027857d8"
msgstr ""
"That which neither roams within saṃsāra nor passes into complete nirvāṇa is "
"not past, future, or present."

msgid "9ce93b5b6f7243a49b37fc08f7c9df9c"
msgstr ""
"That which is not past, future, or present is not low, middling, or high."

msgid "feb44b7d53b74941a146e9200d603573"
msgstr "That which is not low, middling, or high is the tathatā."

msgid "ec2852dc1c4c4bb1939c70607c2b48be"
msgstr "“What we call tathathā is an expression meaning tattva."

msgid "e0972193087641c584dbd742c78b121c"
msgstr "What we call tattva is tathatā itself."

msgid "5c2ab0780f2b40d3a5ae547bcf5cf95f"
msgstr "Tathatā being the same as tattva is called tathatva."

msgid "690c06bd90ce4dc0b37b18dd659aab3b"
msgstr "Thus, the tathatā and the self are not two, they are non-dual."

msgid "11c0c7d82eee437191bc489b5c08d313"
msgstr ""
"The meaning of non-duality is awakening, in the sense of becoming awake."

msgid "5891f3f8a2284af09fc7a40b28f8eeec"
msgstr ""
"The meaning is explained as the awareness that enters the three gates of "
"liberation with respect to all the Dharma teachings."

msgid "b6abdd2b643340a79e5fb4bd1d83acd1"
msgstr ""
"The awareness is explained as engaging in the sameness of the three times "
"with respect to all dharmas."

msgid "6987d191b1d04cb08d543ac1708f6765"
msgstr ""
"The meaning of the inseparability of all dharmas is what is explained as the"
" meaning."

msgid "cb305807c22a4145bd5ce45f2233a05b"
msgstr "It is voiceless,"

msgid "6135406111cc48039aa472334f28f492"
msgstr "ineffable,"

msgid "af3d9e085c4c4dad8cb2e052636b53e8"
msgstr "inexpressible,"

msgid "49069f9677d84c388fbba3453050905b"
msgstr "and cut off from any expressions."

msgid "fa8fb9c7edde46c2bee8d8582649ec5d"
msgstr ""
"Awareness is explained as the awareness that understands the meaning and "
"understands consciousness;"

msgid "957cd4f6f2d54f4d99439d3c9d2e23ec"
msgstr "this is explained as awareness."

msgid "836f2141a2b64dcda398f56884d5784e"
msgstr ""
"The meaning is explained as the meaning that is established by the awareness"
" that understands the meaning of tattva, and by the awareness that "
"understands consciousness."

msgid "2648d24b168a4cec95f96c58d3a1fb69"
msgstr "That itself is the dharmatā."

msgid "4d90c456e6b64a938ca837b6dc748630"
msgstr "And the dharmatā is the meaning."

msgid "b3479171df6b4b82b8a7335031ca08ea"
msgstr "Sameness is the meaning."

msgid "1865f8c557644d59be7ba44a231c6cd7"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, for those who have attachment to form, the eye is attachment."

msgid "b8f105f164974ffeb3ff53ba69a8b699"
msgstr "Knowing the nature of form and of the eye is non-attachment."

msgid "a8dc0047916e43ea999b254d5010b278"
msgstr ""
"“For those who have attachment to views, one’s own body is attachment."

msgid "ba0990f2f85a423ab3dccbb13ef2e17d"
msgstr ""
"For those who have done away with all views, the awareness of one’s body’s "
"natural emptiness is non-attachment."

msgid "38b2581e9176495a956750a801e23c71"
msgstr ""
"“For those who are stuck in their attachment to improper mental placement, "
"the appearance of dharmas is attachment."

msgid "4628331be54443e18449db5a1ecb04e3"
msgstr ""
"Discerning the dharmas through proper mental placement, the awareness of "
"emptiness by nature and emptiness of essence is non-attachment."

msgid "337a957a81c741fb8824f48c88c9e7fc"
msgstr ""
"“For those who are stuck in their attachment to the stain of doubt, "
"liberation is attachment."

msgid "c37a9269ef5f4537b02468b2ea32d55f"
msgstr "The authentic awareness of belief and liberation is non-attachment."

msgid "6f1a94cd462147c8913e2d199b9c326e"
msgstr ""
"“For those who are stuck in their attachment to the stain of laziness, "
"having present diligence toward realization is attachment."

msgid "fb13fb5ca22f49b1abc1025e2e645fa6"
msgstr "The realization of dharmas as they are is non-attachment."

msgid "eeb0721d18804186a367116a287b30af"
msgstr "The realization of dharmas as they are is non-attachment."

msgid "8dd24108dd504683b57f5af46097c302"
msgstr ""
"“For those who are stuck in their attachment to the hindrances, the limbs of"
" awakening are attachment."

msgid "4285537b7fce48f9bfb1559521146918"
msgstr "Liberation through unobstructed awareness is non-attachment."

msgid "d1a5a80c644b423e8dea726b0e9eaa49"
msgstr ""
"“Being by nature completely pure, all dharmas occur due to an assemblage of "
"causes and conditions."

msgid "ab20f4a534314346b238079fcb53aa56"
msgstr ""
"“The sameness of the interpretable meaning and the definitive meaning is "
"their common meaning, which is emptiness."

msgid "e56a5b58b5ee4a39b7e0d3d401bfc219"
msgstr "Because he is born due to conditions and causes."

msgid "90d609e48e65470ea635f4bc7bfe293f"
msgstr ""
"The sameness of liberation is the same as the sameness of the dharmas."

msgid "8fae87dc6d204e518bd201261f53f8f5"
msgstr "Realization according to the sameness of liberation is awakening."

msgid "2beecf2d65a24132babc8e1f5d87a19e"
msgstr "The sameness of the person is the same as the common meaning."

msgid "53b3b2c16ea6482da82565bf37292bb4"
msgstr "The sameness of the dharmas is the same as the sameness of persons."

msgid "b52204ed06ee4ab3a751c22fb6a26e7e"
msgstr ""
"It is sameness according to the understanding of the meaning; it is the "
"sameness of awareness, entering the gate of non-duality."

msgid "46159c39fd5e4878896a35a752fa0e51"
msgstr ""
"The non-occurrence of the dharma and the sameness of meaning and expression "
"are the same with respect to the non-dual meaning."

msgid "38f6419c8cd3482cbcc7a58392b0d9a2"
msgstr ""
"With respect to that, a bodhisattva should understand well the cause of "
"affliction and the cause of purification."

msgid "5b4a6498919d43ef88522abe8c5b10ba"
msgstr ""
"He should neither abide with the purity of the cause of affliction, nor with"
" the purity of the cause of purification."

msgid "a9931143320342f8bddf09c1a03b42b3"
msgstr "“Elevating self is a cause of affliction."

msgid "a806bae8659e44b6be06484efa6bf687"
msgstr ""
"Forbearance in one’s engagement with the selflessness of dharmas is a cause "
"of purification."

msgid "e2def3de9abd465e82dc1d9e6729e408"
msgstr "“The view of ‘I’ and ‘mine’ is a cause of affliction."

msgid "6a396efead2741b4b253908f10a31f01"
msgstr "Inner pacification and outer non-movement is a cause of purification."

msgid "87f195b5085345c2a220e4224d7bae49"
msgstr "“Thoughts of desire, ill will, and harm are a cause of affliction."

msgid "604e7a884c384f849b72b1e8f9a605de"
msgstr "emptiness,"

msgid "1cd3f14bca7648aa9af2ab8707f81a86"
msgstr ""
"“It is awakening, because in this way one realizes emptiness, no-sign, no-"
"wish; no-effort, no-dwelling, no coming about; no object of apprehension and"
" no-abode."

msgid "c058e9707a8e4a219972ff40cd49026b"
msgstr ""
"Forbearance in one’s dealings with impure things, in one’s practice of "
"friendliness, compassion, rejoicing, equanimity, and with dependent dharmas,"
" is a cause of purification."

msgid "878cb88d3b5447f48181c84d287ba9ff"
msgstr "“The four distortions are a cause of affliction."

msgid "c7498e68df7948c3b58d75bc79dbd7d7"
msgstr "The four placements of mindfulness are a cause of purification."

msgid "faaf42fd3c10420f990fec7310893a91"
msgstr "“The five hindrances are a cause of affliction."

msgid "f276502659ce4dbeaa45e891da81fbfa"
msgstr "The five faculties are a cause of purification."

msgid "c9bd823a70ba4b20a3bc94ea2dde6b27"
msgstr "“The six entrances are a cause of affliction."

msgid "58414320010d4b7d94dedc6f4cb3d8a9"
msgstr "The six remembrances are a cause of purification."

msgid "b8242a2946b24588a158657e811f78ae"
msgstr "“The seven false dharmas are a cause of affliction."

msgid "3c03d95af9464db7a5d1efb95c7928d6"
msgstr "The seven limbs of awakening are a cause of purification."

msgid "5b956d5b2062467ab14480d49bbf9b9a"
msgstr "“The eight wrong modes are a cause of affliction."

msgid "bd778ff01b724ee68087ff7759e7bf5b"
msgstr "The eight right modes are a cause of purification."

msgid "bb9046160e2145ba84d37442909f769d"
msgstr "“The nine causes of antagonism are a cause of affliction."

msgid "a552e0bb2ccc44c783002101c9a1c8e6"
msgstr ""
"The absorptions into nine successive abodes are a cause of purification."

msgid "1af0d334a21540dbb0ea8896ebff8298"
msgstr "“The ten unwholesome courses of karma are a cause of affliction."

msgid "45776f8d29144b8dae0ff1b90da24f65"
msgstr "The ten wholesome courses of karma are a cause of purification."

msgid "6f5bc82bbaa149f1a3c408ae9ba0b298"
msgstr ""
"“In brief, all unwholesome mental engagements are a cause of affliction;"

msgid "b2a8d3fcb7ec43c1909e90fd0ecc6033"
msgstr "all wholesome mental engagements are a cause of purification."

msgid "7197001553cb43cc9cdf84443ce4ebf5"
msgstr "without a sentient being,"

msgid "2a66a4300935481599952f5b532ce146"
msgstr "without a living being,"

msgid "39de4eda841344d2a8c9051bd5b9d083"
msgstr "without one who nourishes,"

msgid "fa16fc4251494e93a7f4c17f5cda3613"
msgstr "without a soul or a person,"

msgid "8f9bd11fe9e5468693122fe90e701721"
msgstr "without a master,"

msgid "4795fb4c7772482aa7c3b89d7f426c82"
msgstr "without activity,"

msgid "12c0eaf6d0b1488c80f963be59ad86e1"
msgstr "comparable to an illusion, without characteristics,"

msgid "94995026edd941879f3cfd75cc5be5a5"
msgstr "pacified from within."

msgid "075fd8d53bd14223b415399bf864fad2"
msgstr ""
"“In that respect, whether causes of affliction or of purification, all "
"dharmas are by nature empty,"

msgid "a0624ca11a244512aa9f36d8261d2975"
msgstr "pacified from within they are utterly pacified."

msgid "6954ae1d0d2d44a380b61ce7d9c99952"
msgstr "Utterly pacified, they are their intrinsic nature."

msgid "9b99026332d241708d487084cf882ea9"
msgstr "Their intrinsic nature is not being perceived."

msgid "e2ec53104e2c4be7a4be76b580a1bfcb"
msgstr "Not being perceived is to have no abode."

msgid "40a7efed57b944f48cfcaebe4b06ade2"
msgstr "That which has no abode is thatness."

msgid "46f0407374274b6b9032877eb25e38d4"
msgstr "Thatness is space."

msgid "d3775dff32904d85b49760e4b321b9aa"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "d92c6c03546b4114988ef54dead42a0c"
msgstr ""
"One cognizes all dharmas as the same as space. One engages conventionally in"
" the purification of afflictions, yet does not abandon the dharmatā of "
"space."

msgid "c09f82556d054f89970a425ff4fdb21e"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, no dharma whatsoever can be found for which there may be arising "
"or cessation.”"

msgid "e1b900a4545043dc80ae11eee0dcb835"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī inquired,"

msgid "558f5474214b4fada1a8a367323703f5"
msgstr "“How then, Bhagavat, did the Tathāgata obtain awakening?”"

msgid "1d8be0dd919f42649c82d216cdb233dc"
msgstr "The Bhagavat replied,"

msgid "645948dfed03440fa70feb25f9c0bde0"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata obtained an awakening that has no root and no "
"ground to stand upon.”"

msgid "c810f2fa3bf24cd98a8213c3e1bf14e3"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī asked,"

msgid "bf65758c94a54a1bb7667b3d0b2cc9a3"
msgstr "Bhagavat, what root would that be,"

msgid "d363f2946129476d9aeafbb3ed77a57f"
msgstr "and what ground to stand upon?”"

msgid "0f41e9bfd30c4f9191042a9157353b0b"
msgstr "“Mañjuśrī, that root would be the transitory collection,"

msgid "2c4bf067f22e4ad4b071cfeeadcbfb8c"
msgstr "and that ground to stand upon the imagination of what is not there."

msgid "48fc730e4915403dbe51d21eb85c16e5"
msgstr ""
"Then, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata knows the sameness of all dharmas through the "
"sameness of awakening."

msgid "f01f246015b440e990f7ec6c88bbfc04"
msgstr ""
"Therefore it is said, Mañjuśrī, that ‘the Tathāgata realized an awakening "
"that has no root and no ground to stand upon.’"

msgid "e401610baf24477a84b7474dfc21c17e"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is to be at peace, utterly at peace."

msgid "b62dcd31338d43c2b4715302379272a9"
msgstr "In that respect, what is peace,"

msgid "f5e268314dc14717b0765ccbcfdd1b7d"
msgstr "what is utter peace?"

msgid "cb07cd0e65b44e5fbac4045926526e70"
msgstr "Inside there is peace;"

msgid "79e491c788084d82bad2d870a68ba357"
msgstr "outside there is utter peace."

msgid "8fc0ff017af84208951fb4888634517c"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgid "7a5a52d36ab84e31b77c6f1b1ef04773"
msgstr "“The eye, Mañjuśrī, is empty of a self and what belongs to a self;"

msgid "e2af2b88aca740ae8b9a5eb58bb1060e"
msgstr "such is its nature. This is called peace."

msgid "d31921a9e6b6426bbe8cf487da851847"
msgstr ""
"Thoroughly understanding that the eye is empty, one does not run toward "
"forms."

msgid "734436858e3846f792110ee8a0f93681"
msgstr "Thus it is called utter peace."

msgid "f5064bb3c6bf4506a0b991379fc7f442"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, the ear is empty of a self and what belongs to a self;"

msgid "f973b8eddfe843f09703878938e1e350"
msgstr ""
"Thoroughly understanding that the ear is empty, one does not run toward "
"sounds."

msgid "7a66e70245f34681a2d77a451185c724"
msgstr "“The nose is empty of a self and what belongs to a self;"

msgid "cbd7b858f4d045e59a228d59d1b5b594"
msgstr "Thoroughly understanding that the nose is empty,"

msgid "d1748ed3eee6439faba10e7636af1ff2"
msgstr "one does not run toward smells."

msgid "ed7c7a94f761414097fd650018118e89"
msgstr "“The tongue is empty of a self and what belongs to a self;"

msgid "8387eaa878434c76a306308799cb4600"
msgstr ""
"Thoroughly understanding that the tongue is empty, one does not run toward "
"flavors."

msgid "2ba9c036b93841768a1343369d266d62"
msgstr "“The body is empty of a self and what belongs to a self;"

msgid "977b86660bff404e98c0c7997d7fb5e7"
msgstr "Thoroughly understanding that the body is empty,"

msgid "11d2dd33a6434de5877de2c7421eabdf"
msgstr "one does not run toward touchable things."

msgid "3b6c4a7ac83548d69aa6ad257e6cc85c"
msgstr "“The mind, Mañjuśrī, is empty of a self and what belongs to a self;"

msgid "9748065b33f3485597e01117422c98c0"
msgstr "Thoroughly understanding that the mind is empty,"

msgid "d8451168e63e4cfda11fdf3beb466980"
msgstr "one does not run toward dharmas."

msgid "73f497bf2a6b4fd6a2802653a5ccdd50"
msgstr "The nature is not afflicted;"

msgid "b5fddb82db3449628369b42987b2135f"
msgstr ""
"“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is by nature luminous, because the mind is by nature "
"luminous; that is why it is said to be luminous by nature."

msgid "43071cabc8ee41ae921452ad4c786626"
msgstr "it is the same as space,"

msgid "6e7577cc0f2b4c4c8106987b99d080cf"
msgstr "it has the nature of space,"

msgid "a868e60afa554648bc4a2888fe4e5743"
msgstr "it goes together with space,"

msgid "f0e8092ef2ca426691e75f80e59cc259"
msgstr "it is comparable to space."

msgid "966286122cc4414da3b3355efaaa42bc"
msgstr "The nature is utterly luminous."

msgid "dbe8bcb065da4181a16ee8f177b4652b"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is without striving or giving anything up."

msgid "a901b6d05c0d4015b255d0874cc7f2eb"
msgstr "In that respect, how is it without striving,"

msgid "9275fc33fc674d4e894cc348b01b6293"
msgstr "and how is it without giving anything up?"

msgid "bd084baa8f804aa5b376787a645c7f47"
msgstr "Without striving means not to grasp at any dharma."

msgid "295fb3a5f2484d28a71c1c008817ee4e"
msgstr "Without striving means not to grasp at any dharma."

msgid "4c5adf44203c4cab846df9ea2df21400"
msgstr "Without giving anything up means not to abandon any dharma."

msgid "82f8df8d2f344e2e8e8417612dfcaffd"
msgstr ""
"In that respect, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata, without striving or giving "
"anything up, crossed the stream."

msgid "451570507cf24e2fb8ea2d67f7a26178"
msgstr ""
"He crossed it in such a way that he does not see this shore or the other "
"shore of tathatā."

msgid "70ec1e8f4de747c19639102225436b61"
msgstr "Thus he is called the Tathāgata."

msgid "b7990c0b5b8844469b8d087479bb8d5a"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, the Tathāgata realized all dharmas to be free from this shore or "
"the other shore."

msgid "1ea7ca110c5e499899819a2df0bc228c"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is without sign or reference point."

msgid "26879e0abe7d4fc8893a0debf55c134a"
msgstr ""
"In that respect, what is signlessness, and what is the lack of reference "
"point?"

msgid "a9978f7b4c414993a1023ca32aa43c4c"
msgstr ""
"“That the eye-consciousness does not perceive, Mañjuśrī, is signlessness."

msgid "68b070cee08540969ac35a570117ff9b"
msgstr "That form is not seen is the lack of reference point."

msgid "8cc8c2abcd7e463c9fc5501f2b395cda"
msgstr "“That the ear-consciousness does not perceive is signlessness."

msgid "458a603776f94b6db3852e6e3011846a"
msgstr "That sounds are not heard is the lack of reference point."

msgid "02a54fe7d90d4b43aab4065a5fc28db4"
msgstr "“That the nose-consciousness does not perceive is signlessness."

msgid "30f29e90112d42738f161fedfa0f43a4"
msgstr "That smells are not smelt is the lack of reference point."

msgid "8c41fc5d51ce4f9388b0f21b5cd80d87"
msgstr "“That the tongue-consciousness does not perceive is signlessness."

msgid "c9da2c05b8f944b8813effeff9ec985d"
msgstr "“That the body-consciousness does not perceive is signlessness."

msgid "71c52f5c4c7740e8ae927cc29779175b"
msgstr "That touchable things are not touched is the lack of reference point."

msgid "630a6b0bc20941dfb3e6fa30c06604a8"
msgstr "“That the mind-consciousness does not perceive is signlessness."

msgid "a0694477dffd4b7b825708dac3e31ce3"
msgstr "That dharmas are not cognized is the lack of reference point."

msgid "0a918a91e6f942808531fd29c44366e0"
msgstr "“This, Mañjuśrī, is the scope of the noble ones."

msgid "2b83d7992a9c472ea7f4b286d38d2575"
msgstr ""
"That which is not the scope of the three realms, Mañjuśrī, is the scope of "
"the noble ones."

msgid "2588c058c7984bcab359a88f49422799"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is not past, not future, not present."

msgid "c4bb148241fb406e9bc4a6605ada0863"
msgstr "That flavors are not tasted is the lack of reference point."

msgid "3d5b6270926d464a895e9be21a4ad725"
msgstr ""
"It is the same in the three times, and is cut off from the three spheres."

msgid "85fb4f859335488fbd7fef13ca3bd4ad"
msgstr ""
"In that respect, Mañjuśrī, what does it mean to be cut off from the three "
"spheres?"

msgid "48a9fad3f1e846719b6180a6395d6b18"
msgstr "The mind in the past is not perceived."

msgid "8238603094664742af2182309e2de911"
msgstr "Consciousness does not run toward the future."

msgid "b37d9dd575b24912bb769eedfec268c2"
msgstr "Consciousness does not run toward the future."

msgid "84928e85621e40d3a684f53a21a68119"
msgstr "Mental placement does not occur in the present."

msgid "8c13c6f278444487a35ad3446bd7299b"
msgstr ""
"One who does not abide in mind, mentality, and consciousness does not form "
"mental constructs or concepts."

msgid "a1271744ebac4cd09e85678dc0e5230b"
msgstr "one does not elaborate about the present."

msgid "133312e2f7a44ae9b65977e67a8e424c"
msgstr ""
"Not forming mental constructs or concepts, one does not create the past"

msgid "5607e8ddd80e46a19b57921c9b7403f3"
msgstr "does not think of the future;"

msgid "404e9d0ab5c14d728d6c005354a88264"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is bodiless and unproduced."

msgid "49d51ecc532447f3837be06a7e7bdad4"
msgstr ""
"In that respect, Mañjuśrī, bodilessness is what cannot be cognized by the "
"eye consciousness,"

msgid "6b7dc557e505403591c514c2f5cab038"
msgstr ""
"what cannot be cognized by the ear, nose, tongue, body, or mind "
"consciousness."

msgid "05dcf1592222418d8a8059d3923b2a38"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, that which cannot be cognized by mind, mentality, and "
"consciousness is unproduced."

msgid "2b0edf9584a342dca655f4d05ae6ded1"
msgstr "no abiding,"

msgid "a3168e10b5d7440093539d313390c295"
msgstr "The unproduced is explained this way: where there is no arising,"

msgid "c8ac4bf95d4547d7afd97a08849cd682"
msgstr "no passing away,"

msgid "b50ec85458d2419284c41b844827638b"
msgstr "that is called the unproduced purified of the three spheres."

msgid "efcb302e837a43a2b75a2e38c92c38a9"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "8617d4b9e079400083671234a6ae9959"
msgstr "The co-produced should be understood just like the unproduced."

msgid "29c9098dcb314d30b51483c9d2e2c8dc"
msgstr "The essence of all dharmas is no-essence;"

msgid "c945ab6e97b74e92a74d03df1403b760"
msgstr "in that respect, there is no duality."

msgid "55d92c39e8ef44dc9942ca59baae9065"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is a basis of non-division."

msgid "120ec21b74924e028c9a1450fe785bb9"
msgstr "In that respect, what is non-division,"

msgid "8c9d5c65e7e3402591cd438fb786175d"
msgstr "hat is the basis?"

msgid "ff66d417cfe740b8b5ba6e650bd3ac90"
msgstr "No-notion is non-division."

msgid "b449eeab077a49b4a4bbcd5751d13f84"
msgstr "The tathatā is the basis."

msgid "c0ce4d0cb5a44f62981b1b48d2b6b76c"
msgstr "No-ground-to-stand-upon is non-division."

msgid "7eda78d39a07409fa091db43c1f1844f"
msgstr "The dharmadhātu is the basis."

msgid "f440cce43966467fb6e596babe26d578"
msgstr "Non-multiplicity is non-division."

msgid "7b431eae5be943a48338ebe81141c33e"
msgstr "Emptiness is non-division."

msgid "6679098a7b2e40eb9cf7ffaffbbf1a54"
msgstr "The true limit is the basis."

msgid "b59b0227671f4fe6b6b40d36889f2177"
msgstr "Non-apprehension is non-division."

msgid "c31bd1844f184b9f9971342e125bf493"
msgstr "Non-movement is the basis."

msgid "0feb075806144f72a528ee834c302167"
msgstr "No-sign is the basis."

msgid "cbd530f2325f44659b5ac89d5ec12629"
msgstr "Non-deliberation is non-division."

msgid "7117ea78ad7e42f7b77bbcb3627fdde8"
msgstr "No-wish is the basis."

msgid "8c38d2fd3ed54313b1747fe866d56f57"
msgstr "Being without a sentient being is the basis."

msgid "5d44826fe3eb4ffa855a194f90026f30"
msgstr "Non-essence of a sentient being is non-division."

msgid "1b7d72a383fd4892836b6a24806af6f6"
msgstr "Space is the basis."

msgid "18c2ca4333f44d5c89201f988edbbd94"
msgstr "Non-perception is non-division."

msgid "049d74cd531c4ac3a63ed6672b0c99ed"
msgstr "Non-arising is the basis."

msgid "027d54b71fb14d63b500c4e5183c91e0"
msgstr "Non-cessation is non-division."

msgid "75baca3ac6154d5ebf063428e8528212"
msgstr "The unproduced is the basis."

msgid "b450c752498e4c999f35aaa11726069d"
msgstr "The unproduced is the basis."

msgid "0978f6edb0764b15afc3044a47c9c7fa"
msgstr "No moving about is non-division."

msgid "8890f699af584b99bc4ae74b7bbce855"
msgstr "Awakening is the basis."

msgid "4d93c4cec75d4f7fadae0bb951398554"
msgstr "Pacification is non-division."

msgid "f49cc7d7ffbf493bb9e1f87f532ea0a7"
msgstr "Nirvāṇa is the basis."

msgid "a285bcad74c04ab8a41b7b1efb3bfcff"
msgstr "Non-development is non-division;"

msgid "4e07cb32a8ae433e96802ec79dc9a152"
msgstr "non-birth is the basis."

msgid "da4df787216b48e5855e32b48097ae85"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "c0be3932bac44b5e90cf4781139ef521"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is not realized by the body"

msgid "01215c9b593f468880697b9d3a9a8507"
msgstr "nor by the mind."

msgid "211562033ce449579ad6867134bc391b"
msgstr "The body, Mañjuśrī, is inert, motionless, and insentient."

msgid "4f1ecee9dd974d9bb262ee05ab18098a"
msgstr "It is similar and comparable to grass, logs of wood, walls, or clay."

msgid "14c1d7e0c59d4ae1a43d3aaa6014f0cb"
msgstr "“The mind, on the other hand, can be compared to an illusion."

msgid "eafc45ebdc1f4888932293aeb2e79c16"
msgstr "It is hollow, void, unreal, and unproduced."

msgid "ed781fe8c15543d288322b7422639200"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, to realize the body and mind in this manner is explained as "
"awakening."

msgid "78892822552840d8a026206ffbe1af98"
msgstr ""
"This is based on conventional usage, but it is not in the ultimate sense."

msgid "012d6b2bf3594fffa0869d71462cbb6b"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, awakening cannot be explained in terms of the body, the mind, or "
"dharma, non-dharma, real, unreal, truth, or falsity."

msgid "5ea3eb37cc9a4b3eae5a2c39bc55aba8"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, cannot be expressed through any dharma."

msgid "aa15e3ad12be4d1194b121e71d4c1b3f"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, awakening does not have the slightest location that allows it to "
"enter conventional usage."

msgid "d6b88561d73046569d0637e73fec9f43"
msgstr "In the same way, Mañjuśrī, awakening has no location;"

msgid "6df7014f3b8842b0a1d24fe6bfa91e07"
msgstr "space has no location;"

msgid "abc3dc39e61d41b5bf8efac78e3830f0"
msgstr "it is unproduced,"

msgid "4366ae8af1524b5a95cb23341992c567"
msgstr "non-arisen,"

msgid "0611cc3eb0bd498aaf9798ac2e8b1026"
msgstr "unceasing,"

msgid "b5b901d586d1483f9f615d1dc8057678"
msgstr "cannot be expressed."

msgid "34e09a8e763e479a8412fc98cc4b0d40"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, when searching for the real space, it cannot be explained through "
"any dharma."

msgid "f2eaf78911c144b586e4288897292caf"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, when searching for the real awakening, it cannot be explained "
"through any dharma."

msgid "8b8b00d454a24576993830af709c1071"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, with respect to what is real, no words can be found, because it is"
" non-arisen and unceasing."

msgid "f71d59dbeb93407eb8af83b29913b64c"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, means to be ungraspable and to have no abode."

msgid "11c8e4fc922e49a58d41793360815f13"
msgstr "In that respect, Mañjuśrī, what is it to be ungraspable,"

msgid "9936780a6f8a4c748f20a7d9174813a2"
msgstr "what is it to have no abode?"

msgid "ac170de765314c21b9ac6e86eb2631da"
msgstr "what is it to have no abode?"

msgid "b93f5273205d4a928380cf069b62bf2c"
msgstr "The thorough cognition of the eye, Mañjuśrī, is to be ungraspable."

msgid "5d3293c61ceb4bb08de690a87ea827a2"
msgstr "The non-perception of form is to have no abode."

msgid "82f1aee1ba4f41e1b7ea5a33956adc87"
msgstr "The thorough cognition of the ear is to be ungraspable."

msgid "efd4d739be1442549a7be747ce4b7182"
msgstr "The non-perception of sound is to have no abode."

msgid "24e8d7fb5aa94af1a67b4d5a32929349"
msgstr "The thorough cognition of the nose is to be ungraspable."

msgid "81e953944a9c4e3ca4afaffe341f58c6"
msgstr "The non-perception of smell is to have no abode."

msgid "6ef08d4febde477f8909170a177db517"
msgstr "The thorough cognition of the tongue is to be ungraspable."

msgid "61c2703784a94ed0be9dbd050eb1e1d3"
msgstr "The non-perception of flavor is to have no abode."

msgid "cf53d48eb0064873a0ec55596f9d2fd4"
msgstr "The thorough cognition of the body is to be ungraspable."

msgid "971ef3f8a54a492499c348afba41b87c"
msgstr "The non-perception of touchable things is to have no abode."

msgid "78859c40d8b24dd2948483c1847f3efe"
msgstr "The thorough cognition of the mind is to be ungraspable."

msgid "bd07659aea1f4b8a8c9c7104b628c70a"
msgstr "The non-perception of dharmas is to have no abode."

msgid "db47dfe321054c4dae47eb8a8b062a67"
msgstr ""
"In this way, the Tathāgata has realized awakening, ungraspable and without "
"abode."

msgid "1ecc5ecc32e448a5aac3da3069d8e64a"
msgstr "the eye-consciousness has no ground to stand upon."

msgid "724a808698374efabe2558d38de01a63"
msgstr "Not grasping at the ear and"

msgid "57e3f69d872945e3bb3309a6a3b72f27"
msgstr ""
"not perceiving sounds, the ear-consciousness has no ground to stand upon."

msgid "f62ce47fc19245f5bec4539b6d69b5f5"
msgstr "Not grasping at the nose and"

msgid "07f1da20a0334d4eb9cd2618a8b01b16"
msgstr ""
"not perceiving smells, the nose-consciousness has no ground to stand upon."

msgid "3d287a3050aa41fd917f31c3fdac1e77"
msgstr "Not grasping at the body and"

msgid "c54c057287e645158e0e1d51533debcf"
msgstr ""
"not perceiving touchable things, the body-consciousness has no ground to "
"stand upon."

msgid "597e61509c594823a59c9b8bbe021c66"
msgstr "Not grasping at the mind and"

msgid "2512d93a9c814d8fa294ded5c3e571f1"
msgstr ""
"not perceiving dharmas, the mind-consciousness has no ground to stand upon."

msgid "290d8919d839476b8fa48e465f549387"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, as his consciousness has no ground to stand upon, he comes to be "
"counted as the Tathāgata, the Arhat, the Perfect and Complete Buddha."

msgid "9e16d2710dfa4aa6807c6f6ee71b0a3f"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, there are four grounds for the minds of sentient beings to stand "
"upon."

msgid "d7a372f5337e40ddacd03277342d2ff4"
msgstr "Which four?"

msgid "6127a133c5664bceb547af68201a0cfa"
msgstr "Form is a ground for the mind of sentient beings to stand upon."

msgid "024da48d42344224a7c841f86af24b33"
msgstr "Similarly,"

msgid "6e153a595eee40c4aaeb43f70911424a"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, feeling, notion, and co-producing factors are grounds for the "
"minds of sentient beings to stand upon."

msgid "80113da7335349b8a5984026d84ec12f"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, these four grounds for the mind to stand upon are known by the "
"Tathāgata to be non-arisen and unceasing."

msgid "8a6629b9a8b0400baeaaa73f4caae589"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, these four grounds for the mind to stand upon are known by the "
"Tathāgata to be non-arisen and unceasing."

msgid "1d787b5508c040d2a55648e710219ce1"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is an appellation for emptiness."

msgid "b48b499334eb464a939edc2add87ec80"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, the emptiness by which awakening is empty is also the emptiness by"
" which all dharmas are empty."

msgid "5d037630aef2422ca936109ad94d12b2"
msgstr ""
"And the Tathāgata realized them, precisely in the way in which they are "
"empty."

msgid "a0f6f342643e4fe58251410ae7f4b130"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, it is not that emptiness is realized through emptiness."

msgid "d0ff3958a2a64400a03b99b5e73fb125"
msgstr "there is one single method: emptiness, or awakening."

msgid "89de2a0731e74b95b4976fc0d76ff3e5"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "786359f474314b139160daab62ebea8f"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, where there is no emptiness, there is no awakening."

msgid "8f5c283e6751461ebdb9f0ce0e2105a0"
msgstr ""
"In that respect, Mañjuśrī, there is no duality by which emptiness and "
"awakening could be made into two."

msgid "d90d931daed04cd6a005f17a43d98a93"
msgstr "Mañjuśrī, all dharmas are non-dual,"

msgid "109eaf29dcf1415cbed76d3bcb0440bb"
msgstr "without characteristics, not made into two,"

msgid "d5b36765de3c4705936e8d28573feb6e"
msgstr "without names,"

msgid "9d218e2aa675499ea359ae0654ddf82b"
msgstr "without signs,"

msgid "993727963bd54c65a60ffd3e72c68136"
msgstr "free from mind, mentality, and consciousness,"

msgid "c5aba2b06538491f9affa1b1cace3c83"
msgstr "non-arisen"

msgid "0251804a15ef4a3896bd6f060eb49e88"
msgstr "unceasing,"

msgid "5ff6033136284dcf8a43bf67c0dc3025"
msgstr "not acting,"

msgid "4f02abd06ca446229238904fe5a16c5a"
msgstr "not moving forth,"

msgid "0e250dfbce1f4806b18085c90603cb7a"
msgstr "not occurring,"

msgid "1e274abfb6f74017b053572f7566e70e"
msgstr "without syllables,"

msgid "43234b2a2bf04fa59838107b95832d9b"
msgstr "without speech."

msgid "b545564ee1114425b4a607ca03a5ccfa"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, that which is called empty is an appellation for no attachment and"
" no grasping."

msgid "177278070d6049fea8928ea326a42509"
msgstr ""
"On the other hand, Mañjuśrī, in the ultimate sense, no dharma called empty "
"is there to be perceived."

msgid "8886ccea09c54db4823cd247600b0b71"
msgstr "On the other hand, Mañjuśrī,"

msgid "33c1c36f93e441ccb3d7ce726207d594"
msgstr "the sky is called sky, yet the sky cannot be expressed."

msgid "149867cbd7824a979e6d88d143249232"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, Mañjuśrī, we say ‘empty, empty’ as an entrance to "
"inexpressible, empty things."

msgid "c7130ea0a11c4b0db5c818f378e090dd"
msgstr "“All dharmas are nameless,"

msgid "dbde430f32ff4ceea9643d8bc81e9fb8"
msgstr "yet all dharmas are described through names."

msgid "0fa929a1939f4805803f5c70c7f7c56f"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, a name is not placed in either a primary or an intermediate "
"location."

msgid "6bb69f5952fd4edd9f7974c4fb097e8f"
msgstr "without characteristics,"

msgid "8c1fccc9eefd4f94a84439a54f7f5fd6"
msgstr ""
"“Thus, Mañjuśrī, all the dharmas are known by the Tathāgata to be, from the "
"very beginning, unborn, non-arisen,"

msgid "7f5617c89c284cec9e026cea3461e8f2"
msgstr "free from mind, mentality, and consciousness,"

msgid "395b35534dbb4958ae2248b174439e8b"
msgstr "without syllables,"

msgid "8cd0a3c6ee084215bece7a1e1e9e6947"
msgstr "without voice."

msgid "97e6ffa67151471782f9b8bd20926b0d"
msgstr "They are known to be just free."

msgid "87f2b5c15815473182469740abd55359"
msgstr "it is not that they are first bound and then freed."

msgid "0561f575fdf14bb8b3d326709bcc2853"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is the same as the sky."

msgid "8a544fa6e3f844fe8e05c73e2fd0534f"
msgstr "The sky is neither even nor uneven."

msgid "0f94934f6f724f008b8928756797806d"
msgstr "Awakening, too, is neither even nor uneven."

msgid "0013b6b90a184ecd9b18073b5b55601f"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "def2e577e59b4f4aa6c819f47a4fbfaf"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, a dharma with no real perfection cannot be spoken of as either "
"even or uneven."

msgid "f5136927e832425f90876f4c79a36fc0"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, Mañjuśrī, all dharmas are realized by the Tathāgata as neither "
"even nor uneven."

msgid "f3a0c9414cef4b7a857390c9b7666f1d"
msgstr ""
"They are realized in such a way that not even an atom is made even or "
"uneven."

msgid "ef38b571865a4cb1b28a665c4556e0db"
msgstr "Dharmas are cognized just as they are."

msgid "76ad84718a024c8783a24c2698190c26"
msgstr "“And how does that accord with the awareness of reality?"

msgid "7a08825d1a9846f5b64c628ee380e1af"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, all dharmas, non-arisen and unceasing, come into being after "
"having not existed."

msgid "0e87265c44284053970f039e1e735e6f"
msgstr ""
"Just like awakening, so also feeling, notion, co-producing factors, and "
"consciousness do not swerve from the tathatā."

msgid "ff4fc40853fa415ca9e7e17ad63173c3"
msgstr "In that respect, Mañjuśrī, what is a consistent basis?"

msgid "2e989456baf04c639c879e7b677f8160"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, just like awakening, so also form does not swerve from the "
"tathatā."

msgid "40d9c48fe89c4e29825372364d4e9fc0"
msgstr ""
"In this way, Mañjuśrī, they come into existence and go out of existence."

msgid "3ae2a368b32e4f38972004e5bde459a7"
msgstr ""
"Thus it is said that the Tathāgata teaches the Dharma for the sake of "
"cutting off the dharmas."

msgid "41e7b9d4ee6941ec8f072a08b0570817"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is a consistent basis."

msgid "62a3a75fd28d468387cda2afe7120680"
msgstr ""
"Just like awakening, so also feeling, notion, co-producing factors, and "
"consciousness do not swerve from the tathatā."

msgid "b3661c76becf46c0a30a085b13af5f14"
msgstr ""
"Just like awakening, so also the earth element does not swerve from the "
"tathatā."

msgid "3d3e01ac329c4da2b63316bd4008da64"
msgstr "Just like awakening, so also the water element,"

msgid "f3c7fc99acf94b3d976befd856987d3c"
msgstr "the heat element,"

msgid "68ebd05af2b2447798bc8514f46aa056"
msgstr "the wind element do not swerve from the tathatā."

msgid "10f6f40253d244b9998f22510ea0d338"
msgstr "“Just like awakening, so also the eye-base,"

msgid "ae7868726c6b4306a1ec05fa0f3c1294"
msgstr "the eye-consciousness-base do not swerve from the tathatā."

msgid "4bf4c84cf4024930b0ac4a911500e461"
msgstr "Just like awakening, Mañjuśrī, the ear-base,"

msgid "9d0f4f76d6ce43088cb72493465cec57"
msgstr "the sound-base,"

msgid "a85c11d8c2ee497d8726ba25d0f2b284"
msgstr "the ear-consciousness-base,"

msgid "eb0171f52afa4f95ab1850596682b666"
msgstr "the nose-base,"

msgid "9509e523220c46d4b5c7fec297f58004"
msgstr "the smell-base,"

msgid "58353a1724f64aeab1f38da765baeec6"
msgstr "the nose-consciousness-base,"

msgid "5caf96aab44241ee88ba37d94e28e621"
msgstr "the tongue-base,"

msgid "c5d6ed461c944e5c831daa580c949ba0"
msgstr "the flavor-base,"

msgid "413abb1b03284d8ea774cb460a963541"
msgstr "the tongue-consciousness-base,"

msgid "a1e981d1e0894ee395a706085949d73f"
msgstr "the body-base,"

msgid "4f2c4a3d599d47dd8ae3b55652646982"
msgstr "the touchable-base,"

msgid "cdafc8537f8d4b11a697ed15ca7adc72"
msgstr "the body-consciousness-base,"

msgid "406eaf6d714f4effbbdb87a5428dafb5"
msgstr "the mind-base,"

msgid "0379fb21e96e41628d8980b600b7d81e"
msgstr "the dharma-base,"

msgid "64a69a7393b0407195bc7b6f2caa439e"
msgstr "the mind-consciousness-base do not swerve from the tathatā."

msgid "e0d8e802194a490ea17ef682884a92b3"
msgstr "“And dharmas can be designated"

msgid "1f670a6ca8814fef8876e61242814714"
msgstr "just as this: the aggregates,"

msgid "c299825286ef47f2afd8333db85165e9"
msgstr "the bases, and"

msgid "80cc9b67c5074c83bff22fb198cef630"
msgstr "the entrances."

msgid "da2aba3097ff49e28ec1fcb776249f58"
msgstr "And this entire set has been realized by the Tathāgata as consistent:"

msgid "0adc22e1429b4d4b8679e90608e2053e"
msgstr "as it is before, so also is it later, and in between."

msgid "8baf8563a3684b28be539af13cbfefc3"
msgstr "It is unborn in the prior limit,"

msgid "b1dccfe701864cdfb81af02e32a3c6c7"
msgstr "not transferred at the later limit, and"

msgid "fa547ef4d37a4b44b9a97997123721b2"
msgstr "isolated in the middle."

msgid "39fb75c66c1244baade2f829f9d7149d"
msgstr "In this way, for all those things there is a ‘consistent basis.’"

msgid "13afd754a48d40b89eb96adfe5261ea8"
msgstr "Just as one is, so are all;"

msgid "ad09fcd6513f48c5b73b35de7381be96"
msgstr "just as all are, so is one."

msgid "b2525c995c5d4ceab2ef9b3730e9258b"
msgstr ""
"And in this respect, Mañjuśrī, neither oneness nor plurality is perceived."

msgid "973a025c6e154bc09732a0eff28cb38b"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, enters the aspect-less by entering an aspect."

msgid "d43457210fbd4251b892a1f1caaca7b3"
msgstr ""
"In that respect, Mañjuśrī, what is an aspect, and what is the aspect-less?"

msgid "05c6d043988a48f1b3439b73d5913d72"
msgstr ""
"The aspect, Mañjuśrī, is explained as taking up all wholesome dharmas."

msgid "4387c027cd8a4770bf24b6ad6dd25da2"
msgstr "The aspect-less is explained as the non-perception of any dharmas."

msgid "f7096606dc814e1d93fda77de9890eac"
msgstr "The aspect is explained as the stabilization of an unstable mind."

msgid "b57746b0f4474e949f9d019b0595b21b"
msgstr ""
"The aspect-less is explained as the gate to liberation of the samādhi of no-"
"sign."

msgid "6be18ebc0a9247cfb9de76a94086ede2"
msgstr ""
"The aspect-less is explained as the gate to liberation of the samādhi of no-"
"sign."

msgid "61d92a9dd3ed45c881c9346b44469fae"
msgstr ""
"The aspect is explained as thinking, comparing, counting, and thorough "
"consideration of all dharmas."

msgid "ce0c64d7f4c04e23b91b24d60d01d372"
msgstr "The aspect-less is explained as transcending comparison."

msgid "4a5e369dc52841818618269cd53b0fe3"
msgstr "What is transcending comparison?"

msgid "5830c725c73b4e28891ca9720e1a6b1e"
msgstr ""
"It is that with respect to which there is no function of consciousness."

msgid "53b1765476ca4aebbb04d2be604ad754"
msgstr ""
"The aspect is explained as the thorough consideration of the co-produced."

msgid "8bdf289625114ea49afa73cf30f42460"
msgstr ""
"The aspect-less is explained as the thorough consideration of the "
"unproduced."

msgid "ae9f4158c3714878b17d696ac91ce3a9"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is without outflows and without clinging."

msgid "0264631e1cdc4925b131c08fce273185"
msgstr ""
"In that respect, Mañjuśrī, how is it without outflows, and how is it without"
" clinging?"

msgid "bb46fa2e32014d7bb09874f1ac5a832f"
msgstr ""
"Being without outflows, Mañjuśrī, is explained as the absence of the four "
"outflows."

msgid "60d97a72621d45d6bd47e6d51fd71658"
msgstr "Which four?"

msgid "30f96582b43f4816b19ae35217ea4b7a"
msgstr "They are: the outflow of desire,"

msgid "99974913d106497da95ec8896564c147"
msgstr "the outflow of existence,"

msgid "f585531ac62c46bb99195bb5a64b7376"
msgstr "the outflow of views."

msgid "087f353ca8cc4b4d839b90be602d8078"
msgstr "the outflow of ignorance, and"

msgid "487871621271446a87885e6226115af1"
msgstr ""
"“Being without clinging is explained as the absence of four types of "
"clinging."

msgid "b098ffad34264dc18d2c138b58ac9023"
msgstr "They are: clinging to desire,"

msgid "a8acc360872b4ea88d19c73515b7402b"
msgstr "clinging to views,"

msgid "9b89844642b649348d49385d6c93ac03"
msgstr "clinging to positing a self."

msgid "bc07843db04c45c6b0b27eb3d3aeeeed"
msgstr "clinging to one’s attachment to discipline and vows, and"

msgid "19ecfe9dd03b4bdcb24b80b5fdb5f52c"
msgstr "“Beings are blinded by ignorance."

msgid "659ab6b024884463b4d50940f1510634"
msgstr "Craving disturbs them."

msgid "201b9cfc6941470fa2b93087706df56b"
msgstr "They develop mutual attachment and cling to each other."

msgid "f14bb178f52f4c778598b3aaa198318c"
msgstr ""
"In that respect, Mañjuśrī, the Tathāgata thoroughly understands that the "
"root of clinging is the position of a self."

msgid "5a4e4c01372b4def8e7c35abd560e122"
msgstr ""
"Through self-purity, he understands the purity of all sentient beings."

msgid "8957b63f8122403b974950e417b44650"
msgstr ""
"The purity of self is the purity of all sentient beings. The purity of all "
"sentient beings is non-dual, not divided into two."

msgid "916b50d302f14a06a27618b81e4be61e"
msgstr "And the meaning of non-duality is non-arising and non-cessation."

msgid "5c31d06ae9444b27842b7a9d1824a138"
msgstr ""
"“With respect to non-arising and non-cessation, Mañjuśrī, mind, mentality, "
"and consciousness do not come about."

msgid "a7d55af2ea6e4f28844e322d4efe064b"
msgstr ""
"In that respect there is no mental construct by which one may place the mind"
" improperly."

msgid "c8ec5c2ef5ac4f7093a9a341d27a0475"
msgstr ""
"In that respect there is no mental construct by which one may place the mind"
" improperly."

msgid "b6b8cc71fa134b5a9bc15965bca6e188"
msgstr ""
"Whosoever engages in proper mental placement does not give rise to "
"ignorance."

msgid "c0390f9fcaa34e2c852a74d86aadc1cb"
msgstr ""
"Not giving rise to ignorance means not giving rise to the twelve limbs of "
"existence."

msgid "b9436bc04a53476bb8c710fbf316591e"
msgstr "Not giving rise to the twelve limbs of existence means no birth."

msgid "43c94e32d97d477494d2c57eb4ca454c"
msgstr "No birth is the fixed rule."

msgid "4bb901c713fd4274a3ef71cdee338873"
msgstr "The fixed rule is the definitive meaning."

msgid "56eb804bedc94f538fd3a9e9aabe4346"
msgstr "The definitive meaning is the ultimate meaning."

msgid "8092b808fed048bf967cf4dcaf068bbb"
msgstr "The ultimate meaning means to be devoid of a person."

msgid "faffda80ef2a4c3fa5678796fa0caded"
msgstr "The meaning of being devoid of a person is the ineffable meaning."

msgid "db34269e8e7844cf8dea890d31a76763"
msgstr "The ineffable meaning is the meaning of dependent arising."

msgid "ad24ba69e216474c8846b9768f7e14c4"
msgstr "The meaning of dependent arising is the meaning of the Dharma."

msgid "3d95be59a9264dc9969ea423d9a2d6d8"
msgstr "The meaning of the Dharma is the meaning of the Tathāgata."

msgid "1f8a19c7f2f84dcfac6afcce2340db17"
msgstr "Hence it is said, ‘One who sees dependent arising sees the Dharma;"

msgid "a025afc0112f44cb91d8d64be646a6e2"
msgstr "one who sees the Dharma sees the Tathāgata.’"

msgid "7b4796d76c794eb7bc8e9c7de83820fe"
msgstr ""
"And he sees in such a way that, when he searches, he does not see anything "
"whatsoever."

msgid "63e4a7c4b5974490900916a334b6a98e"
msgstr "“Awakening, Mañjuśrī, is pure, stainless, and without disturbance."

msgid "83e1820ac2354c03ab5555caef477b60"
msgstr ""
"In that respect, Mañjuśrī, what is purity, what is meant by stainless, and "
"what is non-disturbance?"

msgid "6ee6e5732df74f1ebcfa8d7ec398bc2a"
msgstr "Emptiness, Mañjuśrī, is purity;"

msgid "98601eae5336495c875dcb24dbb7f9a1"
msgstr "no-sign is stainless;"

msgid "d0d8eaecb2104a78a1a5e2abf6ded5d1"
msgstr "no-wish is non-disturbance."

msgid "02969e1aca0b4ae4859ec45a6b8d40d9"
msgstr "Non-birth is purity;"

msgid "4d43e7ac7b11438489b6cef4981df1bd"
msgstr "non-effort is stainless;"

msgid "b42e8afae12a48deaec59b7185e1ec23"
msgstr "non-arising is non-disturbance."

msgid "2f04355057a24070b6dbd48ce65c08f7"
msgstr "The nature is purity;"

msgid "d4034fc34bef42cf8a4da7960c31087a"
msgstr "complete purity is stainless;"

msgid "960e8c58abe54646a6456850d1604982"
msgstr "luminosity is non-disturbance."

msgid "9a0a350427ca4ba8916cd6ec10a33e7b"
msgstr "No elaboration is purity;"

msgid "43dd9bc167ba471abb7a3e366584ed13"
msgstr "freedom from elaboration is stainless;"

msgid "07dc784bcba64a81b5a49b7a2f04c7f5"
msgstr "the pacification of elaborations is non-disturbance."

msgid "18c4e6269fd24317bcf0b23f90c8fadd"
msgstr ""
"In this way, the Tathāgata has realized, through their very sameness, that "
"all these dharmas are equal."

msgid "8734ee46312b4ac0b1ce764b5fc7c5eb"
msgstr ""
"When one does not see the mind and the point of reference, one then sees "
"reality."

msgid "458664d066de403b8f3fdd0f135dda0a"
msgstr "the pacification of elaborations is non-disturbance."

msgid "8f629f2f3715410fb8fe776509334979"
msgstr "The tathatā is purity;"

msgid "e1e4724acb9c40f3a25907a1fd5dccf5"
msgstr "the dharmadhātu is stainless;"

msgid "512691c51dd34aac95098539bddd5070"
msgstr "the pinnacle of reality is non-disturbance."

msgid "c767169ca8ac43e0b96ba470437f5117"
msgstr "Space is purity;"

msgid "c6b952716708457f8c1f3265be21a7e6"
msgstr "the sky is stainless;"

msgid "66f75131b3ee47fa941d8c696cd2039b"
msgstr "the atmosphere is non-disturbance."

msgid "8a2532cec6b3494c8c5c439070bca286"
msgstr "“To thoroughly cognize inside is purity;"

msgid "a32c07c4b9db4657a9663d9f4070d397"
msgstr "not to move forth on the outside is stainless;"

msgid "44f5103aac5843adad750001870fc370"
msgstr "non-perception inside and outside is non-disturbance."

msgid "5c46d6515810456a9e7d93d2ee8db3bf"
msgstr "To thoroughly cognize the aggregates is purity;"

msgid "8b17d2d9906147a89bc8190e3b6dc0ae"
msgstr "the essencelessness of the bases is stainless;"

msgid "d7fb10350fe847d8981364cbe8237422"
msgstr "putting away the entrances is non-disturbance."

msgid "a227e9a5603e4f2983bdde55dc957fbf"
msgstr "To cognize past destruction is purity;"

msgid "a88652fc2ad24fe5b62603445d78160d"
msgstr "to cognize future non-arising is stainless;"

msgid "f89130e5d2af46ada2ea0b49e319701f"
msgstr "to cognize the present abiding of the dharmadhātu is non-disturbance."

msgid "2f2b1d7c811b46a08cfeca45ae28d0ed"
msgstr ""
"“In this way, Mañjuśrī, purity, the stainless, and non-disturbance are "
"collected within a single basis:"

msgid "13c764f9a49c4ab99cd544aee002d426"
msgstr "the peaceful basis."

msgid "040271bd2f314ef580cccb8e40187a25"
msgstr "That which is peaceful is very peaceful."

msgid "a47b86ba380248bfafa056e9f1c6e18c"
msgstr "That which is very peaceful is utterly peaceful."

msgid "86144f03cdbe443c8f688cd9476d736e"
msgstr "That which is utterly peaceful is utter pacification;"

msgid "d8ef8c6ad8134aff9af8589dc46aafe4"
msgstr "utter pacification is called the sage."

msgid "427ada74d7734d69afa42828fcc72105"
msgstr "Thus, Mañjuśrī, just like space, so is awakening."

msgid "6c1b1dc01b3e42afb5ce7add22c6996b"
msgstr "Just like awakening, so are the dharmas."

msgid "ed9a7082bc164e3b9295699eb52fb674"
msgstr "Just like the dharmas, so are sentient beings."

msgid "ced5ed8c29be43edb31e327619e3d10d"
msgstr "Just like sentient beings, so are the fields."

msgid "4e886e50096749d68ecbe9430502ead9"
msgstr "Just like the fields, so is nirvāṇa."

msgid "2b557a5d0a4943e79fa4714c81257977"
msgstr ""
"Therefore, Mañjuśrī, it is said that all dharmas are the same as nirvāṇa."

msgid "ff73701b47dd47bdbfe2e83a42d43511"
msgstr "Since this is their ultimate mode, there is no counteragent."

msgid "e85c719561e847cebd50de6c9e31bc29"
msgstr "Because there is no counteragent, they are primordially pure,"

msgid "c8749dce97734ccc9a48fa3f2bff1646"
msgstr "primordially stainless, and"

msgid "6094d29c84f042e0936033762f668bca"
msgstr "primordially without disturbances."

msgid "4af59856f6ba444584e063c2459aee89"
msgstr ""
"It is thus, Mañjuśrī, that the Tathāgata realized all dharmas to be; as he "
"observes the sphere of sentient beings, a pure, great compassion that is "
"free from disturbances, called play, comes about toward those sentient "
"beings."

msgid "e9ec4f3c03a94e4a9ec177ff5cd7dfdb"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, how does a bodhisattva practice within the conduct of a "
"bodhisattva?"

msgid "51ff2c45d2354f0d9c45d2e1a4eb8be7"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, how does a bodhisattva practice within the conduct of a "
"bodhisattva?"

msgid "cc5c815097454750826e7de07b18232a"
msgstr "nor is he disturbed by utter non-arising."

msgid "6e5bed3f0dad440fb67a3c8cc7478408"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, a bodhisattva does not think of destruction, arising, non-"
"destruction, non-arising, and the utter destruction of destruction;"

msgid "45b1b08ce28d466b88c4aea9c0b6063c"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "32cf3a6c61244d929967eb8db70e7290"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, a bodhisattva may practice thinking that ‘form is not empty’ and "
"also ‘not non-empty.’"

msgid "b79704dce58743dfa84e2e062ffd988e"
msgstr "‘Form itself is empty of the essence of form."

msgid "835776d5e4a748649184651d22ee410d"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, Mañjuśrī, a bodhisattva does not practice by thinking, ‘The "
"past mind is destroyed;’"

msgid "f59f666decf943d39a9173fbd934809b"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, a bodhisattva practices within the conduct of a bodhisattva."

msgid "47020174e3254d268a71d4e7bbf5d7ae"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, giving, awakening, and sentient beings and, on the other hand, "
"the Tathāgata: these are non-dual,"

msgid "40609190861447b0abd0b9689d315b97"
msgstr ""
"they are not divided into two. Practicing in this way, a bodhisattva "
"practices within the conduct of a bodhisattva."

msgid "4f5d556016c6414dbd8208819135112b"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, discipline, awakening, and sentient beings and, on the other hand,"
" the Tathāgata: these are non-dual, they are not divided into two. "
"Practicing in this way, a bodhisattva practices within the conduct of a "
"bodhisattva."

msgid "347ad3f5afe044439af58f1b72c24396"
msgstr ""
"Practicing in this way, Mañjuśrī, that bodhisattva practices within the "
"conduct of a bodhisattva."

msgid "9094ddf5680d4e80b0717bd2673f6f1f"
msgstr ""
"n the same way, feeling, notion, co-producing factors, and consciousness are"
" empty.’ He practices thinking in this way and also thinking that ‘they are "
"not non-empty.’"

msgid "a4d54487597b480e8e4e81fa739d88ca"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, feeling, notion, co-producing factors, and consciousness "
"are empty.’ He practices thinking in this way and also thinking that ‘they "
"are not non-empty.’"

msgid "127d5ec8a68b4c7ea43e855a90f381fc"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "7df420af399d49599b1d600404422c9a"
msgstr ""
"Because mind, mentality, and consciousness are not perceived. “Mañjuśrī, "
"there is no dharma whatsoever that could be thoroughly cognized, dispelled, "
"cultivated, or directly realized."

msgid "64a288a9868a40e4b7570c0f73783985"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, that which is understood as destruction is simply the destruction "
"of extremes."

msgid "e573aa286ab14ead83f86f08b3faba60"
msgstr "As it is indestructible and not destroyed, it is without destruction."

msgid "6286305b25ee479891c55d091441b981"
msgstr ""
"And that which is completely destroyed is not something one should cause to "
"be destroyed."

msgid "d4afcfe61100470f8ce7dc147180b61b"
msgstr "It conforms to destruction;"

msgid "399d6900f22d46dca00b29e515202647"
msgstr "conforming to destruction is the destruction of nothing whatsoever."

msgid "4425b049e80744a09617881d9cadd892"
msgstr ""
"And that, wherein there is no destruction of anything whatsoever, is "
"unproduced."

msgid "44fd008841974c008ad46da0d9b7c563"
msgstr "With respect to the unproduced, there is no arising"

msgid "b699a0a4c81c4e17a068e45b64570962"
msgstr "and no cessation."

msgid "f2937ea589b848349efd332af6e8e8d3"
msgstr "“Therefore it is said, ‘Whether the tathāgatas arise or not,"

msgid "b927cbce44c64ba2a891233272f4d5ea"
msgstr ""
"this dharmatā is invariable; it is the invariability of the dharmas, the "
"dharmadhātu.’"

msgid "f98a07ab9ed749c6bf1703a09044107a"
msgstr ""
"Just like the invariability of the dharmadhātu, the Tathāgata’s awareness is"
" neither occurring nor ceasing."

msgid "952234a56c7b47b88fed7693cdea514a"
msgstr ""
"The destruction of the outflows, Mañjuśrī, is a conventional expression, "
"speech, syllables, sign, and designation."

msgid "273d4131232e40288bedb6d33e5b60ba"
msgstr "Here no dharma whatsoever arises or ceases.”"

msgid "22eaa1977a7844e09075ae8b419a35e2"
msgstr "Then the youthful Mañjuśrī rose from his seat,"

msgid "a3288b0820a6454d877ef52289cbe617"
msgstr "folded his upper robe,"

msgid "8bfe0cca18c94e428b3f6382184a7e7d"
msgstr "placed his right knee on the ground."

msgid "2e76ebc6cbff450bb30158fbf1d09c0d"
msgstr "Folding his hands in the direction of the Bhagavat,"

msgid "cb2b0c91ac8d4408a796fa1e7e828f84"
msgstr "he praised him with these verses:"

msgid "7b40eaddcb4544ccb2abd2f5eb1ebc85"
msgstr "“You have no color, sign, or shape,"

msgid "8a0a3b2e1b7d45c980dbffdca2ab778a"
msgstr "you are free of any point of reference: I bow to you!"

msgid "89016ed1b9f24822b5793cecdc75758e"
msgstr "“You have no ground to stand upon,"

msgid "0667aad2288242bebe8d0321b40832ad"
msgstr "No striving or giving up;"

msgid "a6f17711fd504f08b9ebd5cef7085b21"
msgstr "“You are not situated in any dharma,"

msgid "d8140a19ce0242f289ba53e1dd58b650"
msgstr "Bereft of existence or non-existence."

msgid "ff54e4bd92274f3eaa47570881d48ec0"
msgstr "You obtained the sameness of co-producing factors,"

msgid "a52068133da24a0bb9b357b555e159c0"
msgstr "“Free from the three world spheres,"

msgid "70ec12277a53477ab9f7f1ed8998de53"
msgstr "You have attained the sky’s own sameness."

msgid "f10a71ee180140a3bb7c66aab8a6333b"
msgstr "You are not defiled by desires,"

msgid "76130f3601754bee8c8b2d1a93be2822"
msgstr "No root and no ground to stand upon,"

msgid "1f6ce7824c91416b9e708053b7e318f5"
msgstr "No cessation or origination,"

msgid "73e4ee67768b4e79b3d55a55d655a1ae"
msgstr ""
"Entering the Dharma method in this way, the outflows do not arise and do not"
" cease."

msgid "4b665f05d7ac499692b56610e1486183"
msgstr "he does not practice by thinking, ‘The present mind abides.’"

msgid "078094a0ecd04996b8acbf3bde57da74"
msgstr ""
"he does not practice by thinking, ‘The future mind has yet to be obtained;’"

msgid "208a9831aa7d4322a4f53de1d1c58f2a"
msgstr ""
"He is not stuck in the past, future, or present mind. As he practices in "
"this way,"

msgid "36f8533f4bd0422cbb703fa385abe41a"
msgstr "the Tathāgata; diligence, awakening, and sentient beings, and,"

msgid "995239cfb87f47c1825fa6f33bf0c776"
msgstr "the Tathāgata;"

msgid "f34dc4d381d84845a08d7f791b346964"
msgstr "awakening, and sentient beings, and,"

msgid "ebefdb8661284cd9b462ab4acff8f64e"
msgstr "These are non-dual, they are not divided into two."

msgid "0439bf0ab352405cbaf760c8129acd60"
msgstr "“You always remain in samādhi,"

msgid "29ccc3eae9d844d1a8e3939d8d41815a"
msgstr "Whichever your posture may be."

msgid "917035b860344a90bec1f3d771c953ed"
msgstr "As you move, stand, or lie down—"

msgid "42f7cf62edb046c89cf3098554f93ad0"
msgstr "“You arrive evenly and go evenly,"

msgid "bb765bba913246cb8acac30df2b55873"
msgstr "Remaining well placed in sameness."

msgid "a92d2ee60c8f4bcfaccfd7e1335fd0ab"
msgstr "You are not disturbed at sameness,"

msgid "4892958467164e1591cc91b15a93835d"
msgstr "“You are absorbed in sameness,"

msgid "30764d7a7e4d4569854c16195bd04063"
msgstr "In samādhi within all dharmas."

msgid "b42ede1bd28a45c08e75f38562183436"
msgstr "Absorbed in the sign-less,"

msgid "2e98a4776dfa425291964788bac31e01"
msgstr "“Unplaced, without point of reference,"

msgid "b8d9dd13aa634be18d63299cf70f268e"
msgstr "Your samādhi is the peak of wisdom."

msgid "3d90d0c89fb94ee6af1733c51f75bde8"
msgstr "You have become the lord of Dharma,"

msgid "efcb1b6d29604960b4f257c63a6c20c7"
msgstr "you are free of any point of reference: I bow to you!"

msgid "81b3824806d64a74b90eab1d0458230b"
msgstr "free from the six entrances,"

msgid "c6bc8e42c1cb401e9fe653e67651ea20"
msgstr ""
"“In one instant, you see The forms, voices, and postures Of all sentient "
"beings."

msgid "4e55ed499ae148dfa14b82349ad3aeaf"
msgstr "“Free from name and form,"

msgid "504592e6c6a44ccaa28d76ab81740203"
msgstr "You cut off all causes and aggregates."

msgid "34f11210812947f48e676760e3bc79df"
msgstr "You are the entrance into the aspect-less,"

msgid "4f1da421f1d44b8ebef7e277470cd3c9"
msgstr "“You are free from signs"

msgid "e78af99fe4a74035b56bf7ddb16fde10"
msgstr "And bereft of their aspects."

msgid "7762452fd4ed451d9549215d205b4825"
msgstr "You are the entrance into the sign-less,"

msgid "f8b1d054496940a1b30f801351930042"
msgstr "“You do not form concepts,"

msgid "55304d2361fc470ab9d024b8201a2d7f"
msgstr "your mind has no ground to stand upon."

msgid "b944ddcb1ac948019a47800e919c00b3"
msgstr "You have no recollection or mental placement,"

msgid "77dd7c0d5e4c4c3690bac0315beaedf0"
msgstr "“Space is without abode;"

msgid "d1a64976c10c4254b33406a007f28019"
msgstr "It is free from elaboration and stainless."

msgid "33f90d48936441029f8a2a9e88170634"
msgstr "Your mind is the same as space,"

msgid "cccf22fdafc04badad1945e84f9d717b"
msgstr "“Space is without edge or center,"

msgid "af78ed034700455d9a4d089f02fc57b2"
msgstr "so, too, is the dharmatā of the buddhas."

msgid "481c05567fa546e88edc51e430357060"
msgstr "You have gone beyond the three times,"

msgid "ca802a5703d74bc9874af5ccbc327ef7"
msgstr "You have gone beyond the three times,"

msgid "5c21fcbb738e4f2abd555af1d12f76a3"
msgstr "“The buddhas have the characteristic of space,"

msgid "37cad0e33df246a0ae358c052bd72911"
msgstr "And space has no characteristics."

msgid "e8681b105b484db1a33ef52e53122a10"
msgstr "You are free from effect and cause,"

msgid "b2cb7ce5858a430ea5cc1b12a384da3c"
msgstr "you cannot be grasped:"

msgid "54d7b717ad524d1d9ade8bd8c2688417"
msgstr "“Like the moon in the water,"

msgid "ee549be32cda43619dfad6ac326a4d99"
msgstr "You are not placed in any dharma."

msgid "cedf5e46f4294377b1500a3092a4b1e6"
msgstr "“Free from the two extremes,"

msgid "0f3751bd3ddd45778bf85511f6bf456e"
msgstr "You cut off the view of ‘self.’"

msgid "3ccd4e2adfaa4bfeaa422b899b9a39e0"
msgstr "You obtained sameness with the dharmadhātu,"

msgid "0e73fac2a7b04b2eba61e5adfac31f14"
msgstr "“You are free from form and number,"

msgid "5a87853bccf64206b6f6b2516e370fd8"
msgstr "“You are not dwelling in the aggregates, The bases, or the entrances."

msgid "3b206544158649759d00cf518b7b148c"
msgstr "You are free from distortions,"

msgid "cc33c8bdd0e6466a8ed077720c15ac63"
msgstr "bereft of any false dharmas."

msgid "8d600c6ebb9d491599075f7ea40e46bb"
msgstr "You neither cling to, nor abandon,"

msgid "6fa378eb4ed343afbd30eb88859cbf0b"
msgstr "“You have gone beyond the faults of Māra"

msgid "ff8b885fbe7447beb9549d3ae413bb33"
msgstr "reached the path of the dharmadhātu."

msgid "a50767ac927645c3896675d2557cc723"
msgstr "You have the feature of non-obscuration,"

msgid "e5f85f5f94b74c1aa47fd0a9d8d66e0c"
msgstr ""
"“Those who understand the meaning, Do not say ‘he exists’ or ‘he does not.’"

msgid "58a9d875975049a598b8565b062ba282"
msgstr "You are not in the realm of words,"

msgid "f4651f4ddff14337b79cd6c9031d1e6c"
msgstr "“Not relying on duality,"

msgid "4b00b6bf7bc44b1d89a76fed3d21f16c"
msgstr "You are free from duality and non-duality,"

msgid "2204d8b555e64ff0b1a8e69d32349daa"
msgstr "You cut down the banner of pride."

msgid "a21ee9600b8349f289a811eefe21a274"
msgstr "You are inconceivable, without compare,"

msgid "db480f50c58a45e4a8b95b87c931f00a"
msgstr "“You have subdued all mental flaws, And the four flaws of the body."

msgid "fe1e553d72d544dcb27440af582ee999"
msgstr "“You conduct yourself effortlessly,"

msgid "9e3fc523bcf24fa9a864ee934fd39bee"
msgstr "you are bereft of any flaws."

msgid "0bf5e38d55be47d6a721c635f42370bf"
msgstr "Awareness precedes all your actions,"

msgid "a32c4da0d1a7441393d29ab2c3423727"
msgstr "Your recollection has no outflows:"

msgid "38678f07fa7e498c8ab800b419f93336"
msgstr "It is subtle and conforms to what is real and unreal."

msgid "39abd355b1bc4637a94a982242fc82d5"
msgstr "You have no abode and no thoughts,"

msgid "04c2a02db60f4c75b0071a8f1a54bd70"
msgstr "“With your mind free of a point of reference,"

msgid "f966aca3ccb44228a27bfd74c1b40c91"
msgstr "You understand well the mind of all,"

msgid "28171d869cd944cc859f9f983c55358c"
msgstr "While having no notion of ‘self’ and ‘others.’"

msgid "10a503d470654972b36a80ed835da19c"
msgstr "You remain unobscured,"

msgid "afe073a25d324593bad31e7cca2d87f2"
msgstr "Makes everyone’s mind bewildered."

msgid "04f0367a3ea140eea31cf2cc1a4867ce"
msgstr "“Taking up points of reference"

msgid "f2ee3620ed404dedba7e164539b0b8ac"
msgstr "you are free of any point of reference: I bow to you!"

msgid "95ac62354c964f59a2eba66212342cef"
msgstr "a mind without point of reference"

msgid "ad6565a66e874524b843e22799d5cd45"
msgstr "Cannot essentially be found."

msgid "63867ece2ddd465497729a4e05c929cb"
msgstr "You obtained inconceivable sameness,"

msgid "44afaee39104462e9b2af59a10901962"
msgstr "“With your unplaced awareness,"

msgid "4368fc9defb24215b433911557cf4936"
msgstr "You see all the fields,"

msgid "40399a8d9a6c49788c291bc866e6764d"
msgstr "And the conduct of all beings."

msgid "696e461811de416095a0c258a8c630a5"
msgstr "you know everything about all dharmas."

msgid "bda693ae705d40b6a6856c2350c80d3b"
msgstr "“The buddhas do not apprehend the mind, In any way, ever;"

msgid "c852bda8589d41fbad739bee1d9a7f16"
msgstr "“Illusion-like are all dharmas,"

msgid "ebaff15c34a84c87ad807f08cc1bb9fd"
msgstr "Yet the illusion itself cannot be found."

msgid "8cc3bfb1ad884e5a80bcbe16764dc38f"
msgstr "You are free from the dharma of illusion,"

msgid "c5ed78bd7a2247129d537eea4b0c4078"
msgstr "“Perfect Buddha, you act in the world,"

msgid "de0dc79aeed041308bb509fe410c9a94"
msgstr "Not dwelling upon worldly dharmas,"

msgid "f5e173ae6e024e5f9754a8c79882ce64"
msgstr "you do not form concepts about the ‘world.’"

msgid "09624b21f415427ca074872edb27ff42"
msgstr "You declare what is empty as empty,"

msgid "9ec8de6b261447078a9df50ca6a11f59"
msgstr "You are absorbed into freedom from multiplicity,"

msgid "01fa9edfbe9f4ea380fbbbe59df604b4"
msgstr "“Through great powers and illusory samādhi, You perform miracles."

msgid "475eef8374dd48ae99fa0a3f27a2dd4a"
msgstr "“You are neither one, nor many,"

msgid "918fe0139435454e988846057bd616df"
msgstr "You are neither far, nor near."

msgid "79b99408f0944e8dad55e66e97dd4122"
msgstr "You neither remove, nor add,"

msgid "efe8d8f0532a4911b60685f65ee09d02"
msgstr "“Through the diamond-like samādhi,"

msgid "bc007b938508495cb7a3f178976269db"
msgstr "You obtained supreme awakening in one instant."

msgid "1e16cfebb33b46058966e6216be702a1"
msgstr "You are absorbed into non-appearance,"

msgid "295b0f4633d84247b27555516aa4ad7f"
msgstr "“You know nirvāṇa to be unmoving in the three times."

msgid "64ddcd08e1a94118a3718909f190b631"
msgstr "You are a guide endowed with many methods,"

msgid "ff83303284c64d9694d85a62c7ddeb0a"
msgstr "You know nirvāṇa to be unmoving,"

msgid "36bb0ac85c1b45f8a20ce555321b7dd1"
msgstr "“You are expert in understanding which methods,"

msgid "e60604805e5244a98ed3463310aa058b"
msgstr "“You are free from signs, effortless,"

msgid "6f3b31a10e844c24826f214af52beb57"
msgstr "Free from elaboration, and untainted."

msgid "2aa704a6f86542c8bde38df6ee6eea4e"
msgstr "Free from appearance, free from a ‘self,’"

msgid "32eaf4b7097749129007e1523124aa04"
msgstr "You are omniscient with respect to everything,"

msgid "87fb13a3bdf046f08063395d4ba9bb33"
msgstr "You yourself know the self as it is."

msgid "c89023c313794a608d4a33c3b92d58cf"
msgstr "“Free from concepts, free from what belongs to a self,"

msgid "90787bd72a804f22a4fe325b94148346"
msgstr "you are free of any point of reference: I bow to you!"

msgid "dac54ac276ac4053871c4e7cee9756d8"
msgstr "“I salute you, who have ten powers and have crossed the stream."

msgid "bab546ce9e4d42f3a70bbfe56f9947ad"
msgstr "I salute you, the fearless one who bestows fearlessness."

msgid "e98a24b78f9b442996da651dcb248fde"
msgstr "You obtained certainty in the unshared dharmas:"

msgid "2a20ac0b885f423099aba7e2e4c38beb"
msgstr "Guide for the entire world, I salute you."

msgid "b734a512e7384cf5a1752482cc21d3f1"
msgstr "“I salute you, who break the bondage of fetters,"

msgid "e57ec690ead34720a32743cd32c6a716"
msgstr "I salute you, who reached the other shore and remain on dry ground."

msgid "4add3787aff241989c8a1070937eb3cf"
msgstr "I salute you, guide for the exhausted world."

msgid "f58f6db81e3743b79abe91203f56101f"
msgstr "I salute you, who go to saṃsāra and remain unplaced."

msgid "4f8751d0dfaf48b1a3284d0d29ac8a34"
msgstr "Sage, Buddha, you practiced emptiness!"

msgid "6cbce92737814941831263c878a553c5"
msgstr "You are untainted, like a lotus by the waters it grows in;"

msgid "a0a51c52f2274fb588231139f3383c6c"
msgstr ""
"I salute you, who are free from a point of reference and crossed the great "
"stream."

msgid "2f785fadc1574ff29c8c45ef581ae0b8"
msgstr "“Isolation is the unexcelled state of the Teacher;"

msgid "11cb7bfbaa1e434ab85b824664c86447"
msgstr ""
"“I salute the inconceivable Buddha of great power, Who is the same as space "
"and without abode."

msgid "e3d32bf0170b4a48b397e83093cb88d8"
msgstr ""
"You have thoroughly eliminated all signs, And you wish for nothing "
"whatsoever."

msgid "3f0fd5b132264e54a87d3f4eae2770b0"
msgstr "I salute you, supreme holder of all good qualities."

msgid "8b5b75cd2d1140b39a05c443b33a3389"
msgstr "I salute you, whose glory rises up like Meru.”"

msgid "f86c3c0cc5f141afa60d4f2e5e1c4677"
msgstr "Then the Bhagavat praised the youthful Mañjuśrī:"

msgid "40fe5379be5e4369865630d1f10dc2b8"
msgstr "“Good, Mañjuśrī, that is good!"

msgid "d587a461e5f147faaab842750348b9a1"
msgstr "You have spoken well, Mañjuśrī."

msgid "29dc9b172cba4d55aa590cbdad10aae8"
msgstr "It is just as you said."

msgid "fce6b3d5a6774cffb2e25ae2af2ece17"
msgstr ""
"Mañjuśrī, the buddhas should not be seen through form, through dharmas, "
"through characteristics, or through the dharmadhātu."

msgid "87677d65a75b4b328b6b70795f6d174b"
msgstr "The buddhas do not stay by themselves"

msgid "7adb6eacbe8243abbc03a6c3e60b5d8a"
msgstr "nor do they reside among many people."

msgid "192c43c4e392405691cd3a83b0042dbd"
msgstr ""
"The buddhas have not been seen by anyone, nor heard, nor worshipped, nor are"
" they being worshipped now."

msgid "4e1717bd5887427ca5d8420dc5a7d8e9"
msgstr "“The buddhas did not obtain awakening."

msgid "7edb4573d1634c649de08ce77efe0878"
msgstr "The buddhas do not make oneness or plurality out of any dharma."

msgid "68602ffb9aeb41339637dc071a5789d5"
msgstr "The buddhas are not increased by any dharma."

msgid "ba9124d47927431bac2ae4367d92eb2f"
msgstr ""
"No dharma has been seen by the buddhas, nor has it been heard, recollected, "
"cognized, or known."

msgid "0e4b4047215945cea19c4e8ed1662fda"
msgstr ""
"No dharma has been seen by the buddhas, nor has it been heard, recollected, "
"cognized, or known."

msgid "f591da136f40450c8843d04768a4ad5b"
msgstr "The buddhas have not spoken or expressed anything."

msgid "39506e6cf2704049bb4b05c0034675b8"
msgstr "They do not speak or express anything."

msgid "b712a9febe8b4c9d8aed58382ae47c5a"
msgstr "They will not speak or express anything."

msgid "61e30e1b73484089b2b658c16dbacba4"
msgstr "The buddhas do not gain supreme realization."

msgid "0dbb8a9ddf134d89a30e50a7e360090c"
msgstr "The buddhas do not supremely realize any dharma."

msgid "2b05c2007b724369b097e8f10fbe5c30"
msgstr "The buddhas’ afflictions have not been destroyed."

msgid "341fdb9cfc584493a6ef0a907d3be894"
msgstr "Buddhas have not directly realized purification."

msgid "c1f10b75d29a42c2ae14d432ae181efb"
msgstr ""
"Buddhas have not seen any dharma, nor heard it, smelt it, tasted it, touched"
" it, or cognized it."

msgid "65c8ae1cd7004c80859c7101dad81847"
msgstr "And why?"

msgid "a54cd7b77b584d7981da39a6f7177baa"
msgstr "Because of the primordial purity of all dharmas."

msgid "8af3f00af5b64d4685dc1b13bec420f0"
msgstr "such a person engenders even more merit."

msgid "c84a39b0b618443497bd5df3d0f9288f"
msgstr ""
"All the more so for one who writes down this Dharma teaching or makes others"
" write it"

msgid "05a4b8fd064b41f584587a349847b4e3"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, there are many sentient beings to be found in the great "
"trichiliocosm, whether born from an egg,"

msgid "6588082b5f3d4a88b9a5f3c9dfae71ec"
msgstr "born from a womb,"

msgid "72cdadbdf5a14446ab9b973e1ee7dcb8"
msgstr "born from moisture,"

msgid "83a3082d08e546a6ac006280bb4f9e0d"
msgstr "born suddenly;"

msgid "6d603273f71648888db3f36c3da4c3b6"
msgstr "some with form, others formless;"

msgid "d522f9c172754a95b999ed92d194264e"
msgstr "some with notions, others without notions;"

msgid "67dd5081579547fdaf904b7e48c4296d"
msgstr "some without feet, others with two feet,"

msgid "e16aecb054334c449f444f20af63b910"
msgstr ""
"some with four feet, or with many feet. Now, imagine that all of them obtain"
" a human body, without precedent, but not their last."

msgid "e251870e7c1348df8058c0d95e4e137c"
msgstr "Once they obtain a human body, they give rise to bodhicitta."

msgid "7efa0767062a4f769df902fb042b88cd"
msgstr "Having given rise to bodhicitta,"

msgid "190cb6c88d4a4a65a1763a9d32809110"
msgstr ""
"each and every one of those bodhisattvas attends as many buddhas, together "
"with bodhisattvas and hearers,"

msgid "461901aadab64fb483809c29d9398588"
msgstr ""
"as there are atomic particles in buddhafields as numerous as the grains of "
"sand in the Ganges."

msgid "f4333db0b61742acb0ce9ba710df3f5e"
msgstr "he collects all the necessities for their happiness."

msgid "66b52b9431d04b0b9e97cc9ef6972965"
msgstr ""
"offers robes, alms-food, bedding, seats, herbs that counteract illness, and "
"provisions,"

msgid "5ddb4cc2cb14422983affaad05200a9d"
msgstr "for as many eons as the number of grains of sand in the Ganges."

msgid "d5aa339d0f6b4daab062543ff558e339"
msgstr "pearls,"

msgid "9ac17d4545134814b473b759c5b36851"
msgstr "with raised umbrellas, standards, and flags,"

msgid "e7ab3bb843fe453aa76c1aa5ea4fe070"
msgstr ""
"“Now imagine another bodhisattva, with the right inclination, who listens to"
" this Dharma teaching, The Ornament of the Light of Awareness That Enters "
"the Domain of All Buddhas, and then believes in it, engages with it, trusts "
"it,"

msgid "cb47bc7c2dff460196274648c28f3af6"
msgstr ""
"realizes it, or teaches at least one of its stanzas. Compared to the "
"bodhisattvas first mentioned, he would engender even more uncountable merit "
"that would lead him to follow the awareness of a buddha."

msgid "8fcaededd053434980c5c3b28320feec"
msgstr ""
"Compared to the merit he would produce, the production of merit in the first"
" instance, consisting of the bodhisattvas’ acts of giving, would not even "
"amount to a hundredth part."

msgid "ef1e1457436045e2b65f0d44b243dcc6"
msgstr ""
"It would not even count for one thousandth or one-billionth of it. It would "
"not even count as any part, any number worthy of consideration, simile or "
"approximation of any kind."

msgid "9991586261164efda3f0d092e82f2984"
msgstr ""
"“Mañjuśrī, imagine a householder bodhisattva who attends as many buddhas and"
" bodhisattvas,"

msgid "b4b0432cde9f43be8c5e5944fcd66788"
msgstr ""
"together with their saṅgha of hearers, as there are grains of sand in the "
"Ganges, for eons as numerous as the grains of sand in the Ganges."

msgid "2c4b28f1885a40afaac1c832ffd6e230"
msgstr ""
"He would offer them robes, alms-food, bedding, seats, remedies for "
"exhaustion, medicinal herbs, and provisions."

msgid "186f18e10c194103a51c914534701282"
msgstr ""
"another ordained bodhisattva, disciplined and with the right inclination, "
"may give a morsel of food to a single sentient being born as an animal."

msgid "79bbb0c7632d4af9b2a0989258ced5c9"
msgstr ""
"another ordained bodhisattva, disciplined and with the right inclination, "
"may give a morsel of food to a single sentient being born as an animal."

